recipient_name: REGENTS OF THE UNIVERSITY OF COLORADO  THE
recipient_parent_name: REGENTS OF THE UNIVERSITY OF COLORADO, THE
award_description: CUBESATS HAVE SEEN A HUGE GROWTH OVER THE PAST FEW YEARS IN TERMS OF SYSTEM DEVELOPMENT AND APPLICATIONS. WHILE THE ORIGINAL 1U FORM FACTOR WAS SEEN TO BE TOO SMALL FOR USEFUL APPLICATIONS THE 3U FORM FACTOR HAS GROWN IN POPULARITY AND THE RECENT SUCCESS OF SPACE SCIENCE CUBESAT MISSIONS SUCH AS RAX DICE AND CSSWE HAVE CLEARLY DEMONSTRATED THE CAPABILITY OF THESE PLATFORMS FOR SCIENTIFIC MISSIONS. WITH A RECENT PUSH FROM NASA AND OTHERS IT IS EXPECTED THAT THE NEW 6U FORM FACTOR WILL OPEN THE OPPORTUNITY TO FLY MORE CAPABLE SCIENTIFIC PAYLOADS THAT SIMPLY WOULD NOT FIT INTO THE MASS AND VOLUME CONSTRAINTS OF THE 3U FORM FACTOR. IN ADDITION TO INCREASING THE SIZE OF THE CUBESAT STANDARD DEVELOPMENTS IN SUBSYSTEM TECHNOLOGY HAS ALSO BEEN MOVING THE CAPABILITIES OF THESE SYSTEMS FORWARD. SUCH DEVELOPMENTS INCLUDE DEPLOYABLE SOLAR ARRAYS AND SUB ARCMINUTE ATTITUDE CONTROL AND DETERMINATION SYSTEMS. HOWEVER ONE OF THE CURRENT BOTTLENECKS IN SMALL SATELLITE TECHNOLOGY IS THE AVAILABILITY OF A COST EFFECTIVE  LOW POWER COMMUNICATION SYSTEM THAT IS COMPATIBLE WITH THE CUBESAT STANDARD AND CAN ACHIEVE DATA RATES OF 12.5MBPS OR MORE. WE ARE PROPOSING TO DEVELOP A COMMUNICATION SYSTEM WITH AN S-BAND COMMAND UPLINK AND AN XBAND DATA DOWNLINK CAPABLE OF 12.5MBPS AND COMPATIBLE WITH THE MASS VOLUME AND POWER CONSTRAINTS OF A CUBESAT. ADDITIONALLY THE SYSTEM WILL BE COMPATIBLE WITH THE NASA NEAR EARTH NETWORK WHICH IS USED FOR COMMUNICATING WITH SATELLITES IN EARTH ORBIT. THE UNIVERSITY OF COLORADO LABORATORY OF ATMOSPHERIC AND SPACE PHYSICS LASP HAS BEEN DEVELOPING AN XBAND TRANSMITTER CAPABILITY AS PART OF AN INTERNAL RESEARCH AND DEVELOPMENT IR&D PROJECT SINCE JANUARY. THE SYSTEM DESIGN HAS BEEN VERIFIED AND ELEMENTS OF THE SYSTEM HAVE BEEN BENCH TESTED. SIMILARLY RESEARCHERS AT THE NASA GODDARD SPACE FLIGHT CENTER GSFC HAVE DESIGNED AN S-BAND RECEIVER SUITABLE FOR COMMAND UPLINK. BOTH OF THESE SYSTEMS ARE SOLIDLY AT A TRL3 AND OUR GOAL THROUGH THIS PROGRAM IS TO INCREASE THE HARDWARE TO TRL5. ADDITIONALLY THE SBAND RECEIVER WILL BE DESIGNED SUCH THAT WITH THE INCLUSION OF A SECOND MIXER STAGE THIS RECEIVER WOULD BE COMPATIBLE WITH OUR XBAND TRANSMITTER THUS ENABLING AN XBAND SATELLITE CROSSLINK. GSFC IS DEVELOPING CUBESAT TECHNOLOGY AND IS CURRENTLY PROVIDING ADVISORY AND TESTING SUPPORT ON THE X-BAND TRANSMITTER DESIGN AS THEY ARE KEENLY INTERESTED IN THE OUTCOME. GSFC HAS DONE SIMILAR WORK INCLUDING THE CONSTRUCTION AND TEST OF A CUSTOM S-BAND COMMUNICATION SYSTEM. THIS EFFORT IS A PARTNERSHIP BETWEEN THE UNIVERSITY OF COLORADO AND NASA GSFC WHERE WE INTEND TO INTEGRATE THE GSFC DESIGN IN PART OR WHOLE AS A BASIS FOR THE RECEIVER PORTION OF THE OVERALL COMMUNICATIONS ARCHITECTURE. THE PI ON THIS PROPOSAL IS A FACULTY MEMBER IN THE AEROSPACE ENGINEERING SCIENCES DEPARTMENT WITH A COURTESY APPOINTMENT IN THE ELECTRICAL  COMPUTER AND ENERGY DEPARTMENT. HE HAS A DECADE OF EXPERIENCE DIRECTING ENGINEERING PROJECTS BASED LEARNING COURSES AND IS COI ON THE COLORADO STUDENT SPACE WEATHER SATELLITE CSSWE CUBESAT  A PROJECT THAT INVOLVED OVER 60 STUDENTS. ON THIS PROJECT WE EXPECT TO ENGAGE A GROUP OF SENIOR ELECTRICAL ENGINEERING STUDENTS WITH THE S-BAND RECEIVER DESIGN AND WORK WITH A GROUP OF CURRENT AEROSPACE ENGINEERING STUDENTS TO UNDERSTAND THE SYSTEM ACCOMMODATION ISSUES FOR THE NEW CUBESAT RADIO. FINALLY  BLUE CANYON TECHNOLOGIES  A SMALL BUSINESS WORKING TO DEVELOP CUBESAT BUS TECHNOLOGIES IS AN UNFUNDED PARTNER ON THIS PROJECT AND HAS EXPRESSED INTEREST IN LICENSING THE RADIO THAT WE ARE DEVELOPING AND PROVIDING IT IN THEIR PRODUCT LINE.

cfda_title: SUBSTANCE ABUSE AND MENTAL HEALTH SERVICES_PROJECTS OF REGIONAL AND NATIONAL SIGNIFICANCE
award_description: LINK2HEALTH SOLUTIONS (L2HS), IN PARTNERSHIP WITH THE NATIONAL ASSOCIATION OF STATE MENTAL HEALTH PROGRAM DIRECTORS (NASMHPD), THE NATIONAL COUNCIL FOR BEHAVIORAL HEALTH (NCBH), LIVING WORKS (LW), THE NATIONAL ASSOCIATION OF CRISIS ORGANIZATION DIRECTORS (NASCOD) AND CONTACT USA (CUSA), WILL MANAGE THE NATIONAL SUICIDE PREVENTION LIFELINE (LIFELINE) AND THE DISASTER DISTRESS HELPLINE (DDH), TO FURTHER ENHANCE AND STRENGTHEN THE LIFELINE AND DDH'S CAPACITY TO EFFECTIVELY REACH AND SERVE THE TOTAL POTENTIAL NUMBER OF PERSONS AT RISK FOR SUICIDE AND/OR DISASTER-RELATED DISTRESS WHO MIGHT SEEK TELEPHONIC, CHAT OR TEXT-BASED (SMS) HELP WITHIN THE U.S.  L2HS WILL WORK WITH WEST, INC.-THE NATION'S TOP TELEPHONY SYSTEMS VENDOR FOR CONNECTING 911 CALLS--TO MAINTAIN A SYSTEM OF TOLL-FREE SUICIDE PREVENTION LINES THAT EFFICIENTLY LINKS CALLERS TO THE NEAREST NETWORKED CENTER FOR LOCAL ASSISTANCE.  L2HS WILL CONTINUE TO FACILITATE 24/7 PROVISION OF CHAT (LIFELINE) AND SMS (DDH) TECHNOLOGY PLATFORMS THROUGH SITEMAX AND ICAROL (CHAT) AND MOSIO (SMS) SYSTEMS.  L2HS WILL CONTINUE TO REGULARLY PROVIDE DATA TO SAMHSA AND THE NETWORK DEMONSTRATING CONNECTIVITY AND OTHER USER TREND REPORTS TO MONITOR SERVICE ACTIVITY AND QUALITY.  TOWARDS THE GOAL OF BUILDING NETWORK COMMUNICATIONS, CAPACITY AND COHESION, L2HS AND ITS PARTNERS WILL UTILIZE A VARIETY OF REMOTE (E.G., WEB-BASED NEWSLETTERS, ONLINE NETWORK RESOURCE CENTER, TELEPHONIC AND EMAIL OUTREACH AND EDUCATION) AND DIRECT (CONFERENCES, WORKSHOPS) COMMUNICATIONS APPROACHES THAT HAVE PROVEN EFFECTIVE IN ATTRACTING VALUABLE CENTERS FROM UNDERSERVED AREAS OF THE COUNTRY AND BUILDING A "COMMUNITY OF PRACTICE" FOR CRISIS CENTERS.

award_description: DESPITE ITS LOW CONCENTRATION  STRATOSPHERIC WATER VAPOR HAS LARGE IMPACTS ON THE EARTH'S ENERGY BUDGET AND CLIMATE. RECENT STUDIES SUGGEST THAT EVEN SMALL CHANGES IN STRATOSPHERIC HUMIDITY MAY HAVE CLIMATE IMPACTS THAT ARE SIGNIFICANT COMPARED TO THOSE OF DECADAL INCREASES IN GREENHOUSE GASES. FUTURE CHANGES IN STRATOSPHERIC HUMIDITY AND OZONE CONCENTRATION IN RESPONSE TO CHANGING CLIMATE ARE SIGNIFICANT CLIMATE FEEDBACKS. WHILE THE TROPOSPHERIC WATER VAPOR CLIMATE FEEDBACK IS WELL REPRESENTED IN GLOBAL MODELS  PREDICTIONS OF FUTURE CHANGES IN STRATOSPHERIC HUMIDITY ARE HIGHLY UNCERTAIN BECAUSE OF GAPS IN OUR UNDERSTANDING OF PHYSICAL PROCESSES OCCURRING IN THE TROPICAL TROPOPAUSE LAYER (TTL  -13-18 KM)  THE REGION OF THE ATMOSPHERE THAT CONTROLS THE COMPOSITION OF THE STRATOSPHERE. UNCERTAINTIES IN THE TTL CHEMICAL COMPOSITION ALSO LIMIT OUR ABILITY TO PREDICT FUTURE CHANGES IN STRATOSPHERIC OZONE. WE PROPOSE A SERIES OF MEASUREMENT CAMPAIGNS USING THE LONG-RANGE NASA GLOBAL HAWK. (GH) UNMANNED AIRCRAFT SYSTEM (UAS) TO DIRECTLY ADDRESS THESE PROBLEMS.A NUMBER OF TIL PROCESSES AFFECT STRATOSPHERIC HUMIDITY AND OZONE: DEEP CONVECTIVE TRANSPORT OF WATER VAPOR AND OTHER CHEMICAL CONSTITUENTS INTO THE TTL; THE FORMATION OF UBIQUITOUS THIN CIRRUS IN THE TTL (WHICH THEMSELVES HAVE A LARGE EFFECT ON THE RADIATION BUDGET AND CLIMATE); LIMITATION OF STRATOSPHERIC HUMIDITY BY SEDIMENTING ICE CRYSTALS IN TTL THIN CIRRUS; SLOW VERTICAL TRANSPORT THROUGH THE TTL; THE EFFECTS OF TROPICAL ATMOSPHERIC WAVES ON TTL THERMAL STRUCTURE  DEHYDRATION  AND TRANSPORT; AND THE CHEMISTRY OF SHORT-LIVED TRACE GASES.OBSERVATIONS OF TTL COMPOSITION ARE SPARSE COMPARED TO THOSE IN OTHER CLIMATICALLY IMPORTANT REGIONS  PARTLY BECAUSE THE HIGH TTL ALTITUDE LIMITS AIRCRAFT SAMPLING. FURTHER  THE UTILITY OF SATELLITE MEASUREMENTS OF TTL COMPOSITION IS REDUCED BY THE CHARACTERISTICALLY STRONG VERTICAL GRADIENTS IN THE TTL. AS A RESULT  TTL PROCESSES ARE NOT WELL REPRESENTED IN GLOBAL MODELS. THIS INVESTIGATION WILL PROVIDE DATA NEEDED TO ADDRESS THESE SHORTCOMINGS: HIGH SPATIAL RESOLUTION (ONLY OBTAINABLE BY AIRCRAFT) MEASUREMENTS OVER LARGE GEOGRAPHICAL REGIONS (REQUIRING THE GR RANGE) AND OVER MULTIPLE SEASONS.THE PROPOSED INVESTIGATION FILLS SEVERAL SIGNIFICANT GAPS IN ATMOSPHERIC SCIENCE IDENTIFIED IN THE NASA DECADAL SURVEY INVOLVING CLIMATE CHANGE  STRATOSPHERIC OZONE  AND STRATOSPHERE-TROPOSPHERE EXCHANGE. SCIENCE QUESTIONS THAT WILL BE ADDRESSED INCLUDE THE FOLLOWING:1. WHAT PROCESSES CONTROL THE TROPICAL TROPOPAUSE TEMPERATURE AND THE HUMIDITY OF AIR ENTERING THE STRATOSPHERE (INCLUDING THEIR SEASONAL CYCLES)?2. WHAT ARE THE DOMINANT PATHWAYS FOR VERTICAL TRANSPORT FROM CONVECTIVE DETRAINMENT ALTITUDES IN THE TTL UP TO THE TROPICAL TROPOPAUSE IN DIFFERENT SEASONS?3. WHAT ARE THE FORMATION PROCESSES  MICROPHYSICAL PROPERTIES  AND CLIMATE IMPACT OF TTL CIRRUS  AND HOW DO THESE CLOUDS REGULATE THE HUMIDITY OF AIR ENTERING THE STRATOSPHERE?4. WHAT ARE THE CHEMICAL AND TRANSPORT PROCESSES THAT DRIVE THE BUDGETS OF PRECURSORS OF OZONE-DESTROYING SUBSTANCES SUCH AS SHORT-LIVED HALOGEN COMPOUNDS?5. HOW WILL TTL CIRRUS  STRATOSPHERIC HUMIDITY  AND STRATOSPHERIC OZONE RESPOND TO A CHANGING CLIMATE  AND WHAT ARE THE RESULTING FEEDBACK EFFECTS?

funding_sub_agency_name: NATIONAL AERONAUTICS AND SPACE ADMINISTRATION
award_description: THIS PROJECT AIMS TO EXPAND THE DATASET PROVIDED TO NASA BY PURDUE UNIVERSITY UNDER THE SUCCESSFUL COMPLETION OF AWARD NNX11AI59A FOR THE SUBSONIC FIXED WING PROJECT  TOPIC A.2.5: UNDERSTANDING AND MITIGATING TIP LEAKAGE AND END WALL LOSSES IN HIGH PRESSURE RATIO CORES. IN THAT PROJECT  DETAILED MEASUREMENTS WERE ACQUIRED ON THE PURDUE THREE-STAGE AXIAL RESEARCH COMPRESSOR FOR 3 ROTOR TIP CLEARANCES: 1.5%  3%  AND 4% (BASED ON SPAN). SOME OF THE KEY COMPONENTS OF THE DATASET INCLUDES: PERFORMANCE MAPS  DETAILED TRAVERSE DATA AT THE EXIT OF EVERY BLADE ROW FOR A COUPLE OF LOADING CONDITIONS AT 100% CORRECTED SPEED FOR THE 1.5%&4% CLEARANCES  AND ROTOR TIP LEAKAGE FLOW TRAJECTORY MEASUREMENTS FROM OVER-ROTOR STATIC PRESSURES. AS NASA RESEARCHERS HAVE USED THE DATA TO RUN CFD SIMULATIONS  IT HAS BECOME CLEAR THAT BETTER DEFINITION OF THE LEAKAGE UNDER THE KNIFE SEALS OF STATOR 1 AND STATOR 2 ARE REQUIRED TO GET THE RIGHT STAGE MATCHING IN THE SIMULATIONS. THUS  DATA WILL BE ACQUIRED TO QUANTIFY THE LEAKAGE FLOW THROUGH THE KNIFE SEALS. ALSO  ADDITIONAL DETAILED MEASUREMENTS OF THE TOTAL PRESSURE FIELD WILL BE ACQUIRED AT 3% CLEARANCE SO THAT PARAMETERS SUCH AS TIP LEAKAGE VORTEX SIZE AND PENETRATION CAN BE STUDIED AND COMPARED TO PREVIOUSLY ACQUIRED RESULTS FOR THE 1.5% AND 4% CLEARANCE CONFIGURATIONS. FINALLY  UNEXPECTED TRENDS IN THE ROTOR TIP LEAKAGE FLOW TRAJECTORY WERE REPORTED IN AWARD NNX11AI59A. TO TEST HYPOTHESES AS TO WHY THESE TRENDS WERE FOUND  THE OVER-ROTOR CASING STATIC PRESSURE MEASUREMENTS WILL BE ACQUIRED ON EACH CLEARANCE CONFIGURATION (1.5%  3%  AND 4%) FOR OPERATING CONDITIONS THAT MATCH THE RATIO OF PRESSURE RATIO TO CORRECTED MASS FLOW RATE OR STALL MARGIN TO SEE IF THESE CONDITIONS GOVERN THE LEAKAGE FLOW TRAJECTORY.
THE PURPOSE OF THIS COOPERATIVE AGREEMENT IS TO FUND RESEARCH WITH DSO IN THE AMOUNT OF 99,620 ON CONTRACT HR0011-17-2-0011.

award_description: VERTICALLY ALIGNED CARBON NANOTUBES (VACNTS) POSSESS NUMEROUS REMARKABLE ELECTRICAL  THERMAL AND OPTICAL PROPERTIES  INCLUDING THAT THEY ARE THE BLACKEST KNOWN SUBSTANCE TO HUMANKIND. THIS PROPERTY  AS WELL AS THEIR VERY LIGHT THERMAL MASS  MAKES THEM IDEAL ABSORBERS FOR RADIATION MEASUREMENT INSTRUMENTS. HEREIN WE DESCRIBE A DEMONSTRATION OF VACNT-BASED RADIOMETER TECHNOLOGY TO BE CARRIED ON A COMMERCIAL SUBORBITAL REUSABLE LAUNCH VEHICLE (SRLV). THE RESULTS OF THIS PROPOSED WORK AND DEMONSTRATION WOULD RAISE THE TECHNOLOGY READINESS LEVEL (TRL) OF THIS TECHNOLOGY FROM 3 TO 7 ENABLING THEIR PROPOSED USE IN FUTURE NASA AND OPERATIONAL EARTH SCIENCE MISSIONS. WHILE THIS EFFORT IS FOCUSED ON THE SPACE QUALIFICATION AND DEMONSTRATION OF VACNTS FOR RADIATION REMOTE SENSING APPLICATIONS  SUCCESSFUL QUALIFICATION FURTHER ADVANCES THEIR USE FOR THE MYRIAD OF HOPEFUL APPLICATIONS OUTLINED IN THE NASA TECHNOLOGY ROADMAP [2012] NANOTECHOLOGY AREA (TA10). WE ARE HIGHLY MOTIVATED TO PURSUE THIS PARTICULAR APPLICATION OF VACNTS  BECAUSE TWO ADVANCEMENTS ARE NEEDED TO MEASURE THE ABSOLUTE RADIATION IMBALANCE THOUGHT TO DRIVE CLIMATE CHANGE: A MINIMUM OF 20-30 WIDE FIELD OF VIEW RADIOMETER CONTINUOUSLY ENCIRCLING THE GLOBE AND AFFORDABLE-HIGHLY ACCURATE RADIOMETERS. CUBE-SATS AND HOSTED PAYLOAD OPPORTUNITIES HAVE NOW MADE FIRST REQUIREMENT RECENTLY AFFORDABLE; WE BELIEVE VACNT MAKE THE SECOND REQUIREMENT AFFORDABLE. VACNT BASED BOLOMETER RADIOMETERS PROVIDE JUST THE TYPE OF INSTRUMENT IMPROVEMENTS NEEDED TO MAKE EARTH AND SUN OBSERVING RADIOMETERS SUFFICIENTLY ACCURATE AND LOW COST TO MEASURE S EARTH S ABSOLUTE ENERGY BALANCE/IMBALANCE FOR THE FIRST TIME. THIS IS PRECISELY THE MEASUREMENT THAT IS NEEDED TO RESOLVE THE CLIMATE CHANGE DEBATE AND ENABLE VASTLY SUPERIOR PREDICTIONS OF FUTURE CHANGE. THE PROPOSAL TEAM INCLUDES ALL THE CRITICAL EXPERIENCE TO MAKE THIS DEMONSTRATION A SUCCESS. H. DR. TODD SMITH  THE PI HAS PIONEERED EFFORTS IN USING COMMERCIAL SRLVS FOR SCIENTIFIC EXPERIMENTS AND TECHNOLOGY DEMONSTRATION. DR. STEVEN LORENTZ IS A WORLD LEADER IN RADIOMETRIC INSTRUMENTATION AND CALIBRATION  DR. STERGIOS PAPADAKIS IS A LEADER IN LABORATORY GROWTH OF VACNT FOR NUMEROUS SPACE AND TERRESTRIAL APPLICATIONS. DR LARS DYRUD HAS ASSISTED DR SMITH AND IS THE PI OF AN EV-2 MISSION PROPOSAL THAT WOULD GREATLY BENEFIT FROM A SUCCESSFUL DEMONSTRATION.

award_description: WE WILL: (1) EXPLOIT RECENT DISCOVERIES OF ILMENITE SPECTRAL PROPERTIES TO ESTIMATE THE OPTICAL CONSTANTS (N AND K) OF ILMENITE FOR WAVELENGTHS>800NM  (2) INTEGRATE NIR SPECTRAL FEATURES OF ILMENITE WITH UVVIS COLOR ESTIMATES OF TIO2 ABUNDANCE TO IMPROVE THE PREDICTABILITY OF TIO2 FROM REFLECTANCE SPECTROSCOPY (3) USE THE NEWLY DETERMINED OPTICAL CONSTANTS TO EXPLICITLY MODEL ILMENITE IN RADIATIVE TRANSFER MODELS (HAPKE) OF THE REFLECTANCE SPECTRA OF THE LUNAR SURFACE AND APPLY THE UPDATED MODEL TO M3 SPECTRA TO MAP ILMENITE IN THE LUNAR MARIA  THIS WORK WILL IMPROVE ON PREVIOUS MAPS IN SEVERAL KEY WAYS: (1) EXPLICITLY MODEL ILMENITE SPECTRAL FEATURES IN RADIATIVE TRANSFER MODELS  (2) CONSIDER LONG WAVELENGTH FEATURES IN THE SPECTRUM OF ILMENITE TO REDUCE AMBIGUITY IN THE UVVIS COLOR   TIO2 RELATIONSHIP. THE REVISED MAPS WILL BE SUBMITTED TO THE PLANETARY DATA SYSTEM (PDS) WHERE THEY WILL BE AVAILABLE TO A VARIETY OF RESEARCHERS TO APPLY TO AN REMARKABLE RANGE OF PROBLEMS IN LUNAR SCIENCE. THE WORK PROPOSED HERE RELATES DIRECTLY TO GOAL 3.3 OF NASAS 2006 STRATEGIC PLAN  WHICH IS TO: ADVANCE SCIENTIFIC KNOWLEDGE OF THE ORIGIN AND HISTORY OF THE SOLAR SYSTEM. OUR PROPOSED WORK ADDRESSES THE INTENT OF THE NASA PLANETARY GEOLOGY AND GEOPHYSICS PROGRAM TO  FOSTER THE SYNTHESIS  ANALYSIS AND COMPARATIVE STUDY OF DATA THAT WILL IMPROVE THE UNDERSTANDING OF THE EXTENT AND INFLUENCE OF PLANETARY GEOLOGICAL PROCESSES.  ENHANCING THE FOUNDATION FOR INTEGRATION OF DIVERSE DATA SETS ON THE MOON  THE ONLY PLANETARY BODY OTHER THAN EARTH FOR WHICH WE HAVE SAMPLES IN GEOLOGIC CONTEXT  WILL CONTRIBUTE GENERAL APPLICATIONS TO COMPARATIVE PLANETOLOGY AND THE STUDY OF PROCESSES COMMON TO TERRESTRIAL BODIES (MAGMA OCEANS AND VOLACNISM). KNOWLEDGE ACHEIEVED BY THIS STUDY IS APPLICABLE TO THE DAWN MISSION TO VESTA AND MESSENGER MISSION TO MERCURY. BOTH MISSIONS WILL RETURN SIMILAR DATA SETS AND MATURE UNDERSTANDING AND INTEGRATION OF EXISTING LUNAR DATA SETS WILL PROVIDE A SOLID FRAMEWORK FOR EXPLORING THOSE BODIES.

award_description: PLANETARY EXPLORATIONS MISSIONS AVOID THE DESTINATIONS THAT OFFER THE GREATEST SCIENTIFIC PAYOUT BECAUSE THESE DESTINATIONS COME WITH A RISK TOO GREAT FOR A PRIMARY ROVER. THE MANY CAVES  CANYONS  AND PITS THAT COVER THE SURFACE OF MARS AND THE MOON HAVE IMMENSE SCIENTIFIC VALUE  YET THE RUGGED TERRAIN AND PRECIPITOUS SLOPES OF THESE FEATURES ARE TOO DANGEROUS TO RISK THE PRIMARY MISSION ASSET. THE SOLUTION TO THIS RISK PROBLEM IS A SYMBIOTIC ARCHITECTURE CONSISTING OF A PRIMARY ROVER AND ONE OR MORE SECONDARY COMPANION ROVERS. THESE SECONDARY ROVERS WOULD BE LESS EXPENSIVE  POTENTIALLY EXPENDABLE  AND CAPABLE OF EXPLORING HAZARDOUS TERRAIN AND FEATURES WITHOUT RISKING THE MISSION IF LOST. THE BENEFITS OF A SYMBIOTIC ARCHITECTURE EXTEND FAR BEYOND SIMPLE RISK MITIGATION  THE SECONDARY ROVERS COULD EXPLORE MORE AREA EFFICIENTLY  PROVIDE OPERATORS WITH ADDITIONAL VIEWPOINTS OF OBJECTS OF INTEREST  AND ASSIST OPERATORS IN DEBUGGING PROBLEMS WITH THE PRIMARY ROVER BY PROVIDING VIEWS THAT WOULD BE OTHERWISE IMPOSSIBLE TO TAKE. THOUGH SYMBIOTIC MULTI ROBOT SYSTEMS HAVE BEEN DEVELOPED  FEW HAVE BEEN IN THE CONTEXT OF HAZARDOUS PLANETARY EXPLORATION. THOSE THAT HAVE  FOCUS PRIMARILY ON THE MECHANICAL CHALLENGES OF SUCH A SYSTEM. THERE ARE MULTIPLE ALGORITHMIC CHALLENGES RELATING TO COORDINATION BETWEEN THE ROVERS THAT ARE BARRIERS TO A SYMBIOTIC ROVER ARCHITECTURE BEING REALIZED. THE PROPOSED RESEARCH WILL ALLOW SYMBIOTIC ROVER TEAMS TO BETTER NAVIGATE AND EXPLORE HAZARDOUS TERRAIN BY DEVELOPING AND APPLYING INNOVATIVE METHODS IN COMBINED PATH PLANNING  TASK ALLOCATION  AND LOCALIZATION. THE ALGORITHMS DEVELOPED BY THIS RESEARCH WILL ENABLE SYMBIOTIC ROVERS TO BOLDLY EXPLORE SCIENTIFIC FRONTIERS CURRENTLY CONSIDERED BEYOND LIMITS BY NASA. THE PROPOSED RESEARCH WILL IMPROVE CURRENT DISTANCE AND TIME CONSTRAINED MULTI ROBOT PATH PLANNING ALGORITHMS BY SHIFTING THE CONSTRAINTS FROM THE TIME DOMAIN TO RESOURCE COST DOMAIN. THIS WILL ALLOW THE SECONDARY ROVER WITH MORE LIMITED RESOURCES ENERGY SAMPLE STORAGE  ETC TO RENDEZVOUS WITH THE PRIMARY ROVER BEFORE THE RESOURCE IS EXPENDED. INITIAL EXPERIMENTATION OF THE ALGORITHM WILL BE DONE IN SIMULATION BY AUTOMATICALLY GENERATING THE HAZARD MAPS AND VERIFYING THE OPTIMALITY OF THE GENERATED PATHS. IF THEY ARE CONSISTENTLY SUCCESSFUL  THE METHODS AND ALGORITHMS WILL BE TESTED IN THE FIELD WITH MOBILE ROBOTS.

award_description: WE PROPOSE TO EXAMINE THE USE OF SMALL SATELLITES (CUBESATS) AND A UNIQUE MICROSEISMOMETER CONCEPT DEVELOPED AT THE ARIZONA STATE UNIVERSITY TO UNDERSTAND THE INTERIOR STRUCTURE OF SMALL BODIES (ASTEROIDS AND COMETS). PLANETARY SEISMOLOGY EXPERIMENTS HAVE TYPICALLY BEEN DIFFICULT EXPERIMENT REQUIRING COMPLEX INSTRUMENT AND SPACECRAFT AS THE SEISMOMETER IS A MECHANICAL SYSTEM REQUIRING LEVELING. THE NEW MICROSEISMOMETER IS ORIENTATION INDEPENDENT  LOW POWER AND LOW MASS THUS ALLOWING FOR SMALL MISSIONS TO DEPLOY SUCH INSTRUMENTS AND A RANGE OF POSSIBLE TARGET. HERE WE WILL EXAMINE THE POTENTIAL TO VISIT A SMALL BODY  DEPLOY THE MICROSEISMOMETER AND DETERMINE A FUNDAMENTAL ASPECT OF SMALL BODIES - THEIR INTERNAL STRUCTURE. THIS WILL ALLOW FOR A DETERMINATION WHETHER THEY REPRESENT RUBBLE PILES OR COHERENT REGOLITH COVER BODIES. IT ALLOWS FOR DISCOVERY / NEW FRONTIERS SCIENCE AT A FRACTION OF THE COST. UNDERSTANDING THE INTERNAL STRUCTURE OF A SMALL BODY IS OF INTEREST TO SCIENCE  EXPLORATION AND IMPACT HAZARDS ON THE EARTH. THE CONCEPT IS NEW  EXCITING AND THE IDEA OF DOING IT WITH SMALL SPACECRAFT HAS NOT BEEN EXAMINED PREVIOUSLY. THE IMPLEMENTATION REPRESENTS A NOVEL APPROACH TO UNDERSTANDING A KEY SCIENCE QUESTION FOR SMALL BODIES - THEIR INTERIOR STRUCTURE - USING A NEW KIND OF INSTRUMENTATION IN THE CONTEXT OF A SINGLE OR MULTIPLE SMALL (CUBSAT-SCALE)SPACECRAFT. THIS IMPLEMENTATION WOULD PRESENT A LOW-RISK  LOW-COST  HIGH-RETURN OPPORTUNITY.

award_description: COMMUNITY TEAMWORK, INC. IS A $70 MILLION COMMUNITY ACTION AGENCY SERVING OVER 35,000 LOW INCOME CLIENTS FROM THROUGHOUT THE GREATER LOWELL AREA WITH A WIDE RANGE OF PROGRAMS THAT INCLUDE: ALL THREE SENIOR CORPS VOLUNTEER PROGRAMS, CHILD AND FAMILY SERVICES, HOUSING AND HOMELESS SERVICES, WORKFORCE DEVELOPMENT AND ENERGY AND COMMUNITY RESOURCES. OUR MISSION IS TO ASSIST LOW INCOME PEOPLE TO BECOME SELF-SUFFICIENT, TO ALLEVIATE THE EFFECTS OF POVERTY, AND TO ASSIST LOW INCOME PEOPLE TO PARTICIPATE IN THE DECISIONS THAT AFFECT THEIR LIVES. CTI WILL BE TAKING ON A FIXED AMOUNT GRANT IN THE NEXT CYCLE AND REQUESTING FUNDING OF $300,300.00 FOR THE NEXT PROGRAM YEAR TO ALLOW US TO CONTINUE TO PROVIDE HIGH QUALITY VOLUNTEER MANAGEMENT WITH AN ANTICIPATED 66 SENIOR COMPANION PROGRAM VOLUNTEERS WHO CONTINUE TO PROVIDE CRITICALLY IMPORTANT SERVICE ACROSS OUR COMMUNITY, TO FRAIL AND FRAGILE SENIORS WITH A FOCUS ON KEEPING THEM SAFE, AT HOME, AS WELL AS HELPING THEM TO REMAIN ENGAGED IN OUR COMMUNITY. WE WORK WITH A WIDE RANGE OF INSTITUTIONS IN OUR COMMUNITY SUCH AS LOCAL SENIOR CENTERS, COMMUNITY HOUSING PROJECTS, AND OTHER ELDER FOCUSED AGENCIES. OUR COMMUNITY IS FACING INCREASINGLY CHALLENGING SOCIO-ECONOMIC CIRCUMSTANCES AND IS HOME TO OVER 50 DIFFERENT ETHNIC AND CULTURAL BACKGROUNDS. YET WE CAN ALSO BOAST OF A HIGHLY ENGAGED AND PARTNERSHIP DRIVEN COMMUNITY OF INSTITUTIONS. CTI'S SENIOR CORPS VOLUNTEER PROGRAMS HAVE ESTABLISHED THEMSELVES AS A VITAL CONTRIBUTOR ACROSS THE ENTIRE SPECTRUM OF NEEDS HERE IN OUR COMMUNITY. OUR SENIOR COMPANION VOLUNTEERS HELP FRAIL AND FRAGILE SENIORS TO TAKE ADVANTAGE OF SOCIAL AND HEALTH FOCUSED ACTIVITIES, STAYS ENGAGED IN THEIR COMMUNITIES AND SAFELY MAINTAIN THEMSELVES IN THEIR OWN HOMES. SENIOR COMPANION PROGRAM VOLUNTEERS CONTRIBUTE MIGHTILY TO THE QUALITY OF LIFE IN OUR REGION AND OUR SUPPORTING AGENCY AND OUR COMMUNITY AS A WHOLE IS COMMITTED TO NURTURING AND SUPPORTING THIS VALUED PROGRAM. AT THE END OF THE 12 MONTH GRANT PERIOD, A TOTAL OF 70 SENIOR COMPANIONS WILL HAVE SERVED AT 20 STATIONS AND PROVIDED SERVICE TO OVER 250 ADULTS.

award_description: RSVP OF THE CENTRAL COAST  OPERATES UNDER THE AUSPICES OF SENIOR VOLUNTEER SERVICES, A 501(C)3 NON-PROFIT ORGANIZATION.  OUR MAIN OFFICE IS LOCATED AT 660 PISMO STREET, IN SAN LUIS OBISPO, CA, WITH A SATELLITE OFFICE AT 528 SOUTH BROADWAY, SANTA MARIA, CA.  THE MISSION OF SENIOR VOLUNTEER SERVICES IS TO MATCH MATURE ADULTS WITH VOLUNTEER PUBLIC SERVICE OPPORTUNITIES, BOTH TO SUSTAIN THE VOLUNTEERS' HEALTH AND WELFARE AND TO UTILIZE THEIR EXPERIENCE AND KNOWLEDGE TO ADDRESS CRITICAL COMMUNITY NEEDS.  WE HAVE A STAFF OF FOUR AND CONTRACT SOME FUNCTIONS TO CONTROL COSTS.  WE ARE THE ONLY ORGANIZATION IN THIS AREA PERFORMING VOLUNTEER MANAGEMENT SERVICES FOCUSED ON OLDER ADULTS.  WE RECRUIT AND PLACE SENIOR VOLUNTEERS IN A WIDE VARIETY OF NON-PROFIT AND GOVERNMENT AGENCIES WHERE WE HAVE A MEMORANDUM OF UNDERSTANDING, MATCHING THEIR SKILLS, EXPERIENCE AND INTERESTS WITH OPPORTUNITIES FOR HIGH IMPACT COMMUNITY SERVICE.  IN CALENDAR YEAR 2014 OUR VOLUNTEERS PROVIDED 148,294 HOURS OF SERVICE TO 194 AGENCIES WITHIN OUR GEOGRAPHIC AREA.  BASED ON THE INDEPENDENT SECTOR/CALIFORNIA 2014 VALUE OF A VOLUNTEER HOUR ($26.34), THAT EQUATES TO MORE THAN $3.9 MILLION DOLLARS.  RSVP HAS HAD A CONTINUOUS PRESENCE IN THE AREA SINCE 1972, AND 95% OF OUR VOLUNTEERS REPORT ENHANCED LIFE SATISFACTION AND HEALTHY AGING BENEFITS.  MANY PARTNER AGENCIES STATE THEY WOULD BE UNABLE TO DELIVER SERVICES TO THEIR CLIENTS WITHOUT RSVP VOLUNTEERS.  THE LONGER SENIOR VOLUNTEERS REMAIN VITAL AND INDEPENDENT, THE LESS STRAIN IS EXERTED ON AGING SUPPORT SERVICES, ALLOWING AGENCIES TO SERVE THEIR CLIENT POPULATIONS BETTER WITH VOLUNTEER ASSISTANCE, PRECLUDING DRAWING DOWN ON SCARCE FINANCIAL RESOURCES.  OUR PROGRAM IS COST-EFFECTIVE, SIMULTANEOUSLY CONTRIBUTING TO SUCCESSFUL AGING AND PROVIDING THE VOLUNTEERS  TO ADDRESS CRITICAL LOCAL NEEDS.  OUR COMMUNITY PARTNERS ARE VARIED, WITH A HIGH CONCENTRATION OF OPPORTUNITIES FOR SERVICE IN THE FOCUS AREAS OF HEALTHY FUTURES (HOMEBOUND SENIORS & DISABLED INDIVIDUALS), VETERANS & MILITARY FAMILIES, AND ACCESS TO CARE.  OTHERS ARE ENGAGED IN AREAS OF HEALTH & NUTRITION, HOUSING, HUMAN NEEDS, PUBLIC SAFETY, COMMUNITY & ECONOMIC DEVELOPMENT, CULTURAL HERITAGE, EDUCATION AND DISASTER RELIEF/PREPAREDNESS.

award_description:
THE MISSION OF THE EASE, FOSTER GRANDPARENT PROGRAM IS TO PROVIDE VOLUNTEER OPPORTUNITIES FOR INDIVIDUALS AGE 55 AND OLDER REGARDLESS OF EDUCATIONAL, AND/OR SOCIAL BACKGROUNDS TO SERVE CHILDREN WHO HAVE SPECIAL OR EXCEPTIONAL NEEDS AND CHILDREN FROM MILITARY FAMILIES OR VETERANS. FOSTER GRANDPARENT PROGRAM'S PRIMARY FOCUS AREA WILL BE EDUCATION WITH EMPHASIS IN K-12 SUCCESS AND SCHOOL READINESS. 

SIXTY FOSTER GRANDPARENTS WILL PROVIDE 294 CHILDREN WITH THE OPPORTUNITY OF ONE-TO-ONE DIRECTION/INSTRUCTION NEEDED TO HELP THE CHILDREN DEVELOP EMOTIONALLY, SOCIALLY AND INTELLECTUALLY IN CLASSROOM SETTINGS. IN LEE & RUSSELL COUNTIES THE FOSTER GRANDPARENTS SERVE IN A MENTORING/TUTORING AND AFTER SCHOOL CAPACITY IN 1 KINDERGARTEN, 6 ELEMENTARY SCHOOLS, 3 DAY CARES,  4 HEAD STARTS, 1 YOUTH CENTER,  AND  2 RECREATION CENTERS FOR A TOTAL OF 16 VOLUNTEER STATIONS WITH EMPHASIS IN AREAS SUCH AS CHILD WELFARE, READING AND MATH.  THE RELATIONSHIP DEVELOPED BETWEEN FGP VOLUNTEERS AND CHILDREN TEACHES THEM TO FOSTER THE SOCIAL SKILLS TO HELP THEM INTERACT IN THE COMMUNITY IN A POSITIVE WAY.  AS A RESULT OF FGS ASSISTANCE, 86% OF THE IDENTIFIED CHILDREN RECEIVING SERVICES OF FGS WILL COMPLETE THE PROGRAM OF STUDY WITH IMPROVED ACADEMIC ENGAGEMENT. FGP OF LEE & RUSSELL COUNTIES IS REQUESTING $272,148.00 IN FEDERAL FUNDS TO BE MATCHED BY $37,587.00 IN NON-FEDERAL FUNDS AS THE REQUIRED 10% MATCH.

award_description: QUANTIFYING THE SPATIAL AND TEMPORAL FREQUENCY OF BLOWDOWNS DISTURBANCES IN THE NORTHWESTERN AMAZON REGION IS CRITICAL FOR IMPROVING ESTIMATES OF GLOBAL TERRESTRIAL CARBON BALANCE BECAUSE OF THE DISPROPORTIONATELY LARGE CONTRIBUTION THESE DENSE TROPICAL FORESTS CONTRIBUTE TOWARDS GLOBAL TERRESTRIAL CARBON UPTAKE. THE IMPORTANCE OF THE SCALE AND INTENSITY OF BLOWDOWN DISTURBANCE UPON REGIONAL FOREST CARBON DYNAMICS HAS BEEN A SOURCE OF CONTENTION IN RECENT STUDIES  AND MOST EFFORT TOWARDS QUANTIFYING THE NATURAL DISTURBANCE REGIME OF THE AMAZON BASIN HAS BEEN FOCUSED UPON SHORT TIME PERIODS IN THE CENTRAL AMAZON  DESPITE THE GREATER BLOWDOWN-GENERATING RAINFALL  AND FASTER RATE OF FOREST TURNOVER EXPERIENCED IN THE EXTREMELY CARBON DENSE NORTHWESTERN AMAZON. TO DATE  NO ESTIMATE OF THE FREQUENCY FOR DIFFERENT BLOWDOWN SIZE CLASSES HAS BEEN PUBLISHED FOR THE NORTHWESTERN AMAZON. THIS IS PARTLY BECAUSE EXTENSIVE CLOUD COVER IN THE REGION LIMITS USEFUL LANDSAT IMAGE ACQUISITION  WHICH HAS BEEN THE DOMINANT DATA SOURCE TO TRACK BLOWDOWNS. ALTERNATIVELY  THE MODIS PLATFORM GENERATES DATA WITH A HIGH TEMPORAL RESOLUTION  BUT A METHOD TO DETECT BLOWDOWN DISTURBANCES FROM COARSER RESOLUTION IMAGES NEEDS TO BE DEVELOPED. HERE  I PROPOSE TO USE MULTI-SENSOR DATA-FUSION THAT WILL COMBINE A 30-M LANDSAT FOREST DELINEATION MAP WITH 500-M MODIS SPECTRAL REFLECTANCE DATA TO PRODUCE A DOWNSCALED 30-M MODIS INTERPOLATION. I WILL THEN USE SPECTRAL MIXTURE ANALYSIS TO ISOLATE THE INCREASE IN THE WOODY NON-PHOTOSYNTHETIC VEGETATION (NPV) PIXEL FRACTION  WHICH IS THE IMAGE SIGNATURE OF BLOWDOWNS AND HAS BEEN STRONGLY LINKED WITH BLOWDOWN-GENERATED TREE MORTALITY. THE DOWNSCALED TIME SERIES IMAGERY WILL BE COMPARED WITH A KNOWN DISTURBANCE RECORD FROM THE LANDSAT IMAGES TO TEST FOR THE MODIS DATA RECORD S ACCURACY AND MINIMUM THRESHOLD FOR DETECTING BLOWDOWN DISTURBANCES. THE METHODOLOGY WILL BE APPLIED TO 2001-2011 MODIS DATA RECORD TO QUANTIFY THE SUBREGIONAL SPATIOTEMPORAL DYNAMICS OF BLOWDOWN DISTURBANCE EVENTS ACROSS THENORTHWESTERN AMAZON. BLOWDOWN SIZE-FREQUENCY DISTRIBUTIONS  CALCULATED FROM THE MODIS DATA  WILL BE USED IN CONJUNCTION WITH FIELD-DERIVED FOREST DEMOGRAPHIC AND STRUCTURAL DATA TO PARAMETERIZE A PREVIOUS-EXISTING FOREST BIOMASS SIMULATION MODEL (TRECOS) TO ESTIMATE ABOVEGROUND FOREST CARBON LOSS FROM BLOWDOWN DISTURBANCES. BY INTEGRATING ESTIMATED ABOVEGROUND FOREST CARBON LOSS FROM 2001-2011  THE PROPOSED PROJECT WILL QUANTIFY THE MAGNITUDE AND VARIATION OF A MAJOR SOURCE OF CARBON LOSS NOT YET ACCOUNTED FOR IN REGIONAL MODELS OF AMAZONIAN CARBON BALANCE.

award_description:
THE MISSION OF THE OHIO ASSOCIATION OF SECOND HARVEST FOODBANKS (OASHF) IS TO ASSIST OHIO'S FOODBANKS IN OBTAINING FOOD AND OTHER RESOURCES FOR PEOPLE IN NEED AND TO PURSUE AREAS OF COMMON INTEREST FOR THE BENEFIT OF PEOPLE IN NEED. AS A STATEWIDE MEMBER-SUPPORTED ORGANIZATION, OASHF IS THE LARGEST CHARITABLE FOOD ASSISTANCE NETWORK IN OHIO.   IN STATE FISCAL YEAR 2010, OASHF AND ITS NETWORK OF 12 FEEDING AMERICA-AFFILIATED FOODBANKS, DISTRIBUTED NEARLY 35 MILLION POUNDS OF FRESH FRUITS AND VEGETABLES AND SHELF-STABLE ITEMS THROUGH OASHF'S TWO CORE PROGRAMS: THE OHIO FOOD PROGRAM AND THE AGRICULTURE CLEARANCE PROGRAM, AN INCREASE OF 41.6% OVER THE PREVIOUS FISCAL YEAR.  THESE TWO STATE-FUNDED PROGRAMS HAVE BEEN DESCRIBED AS THE MOST SUCCESSFUL PUBLIC-PRIVATE PROGRAMS IN THE STATE, NOT ONLY FEEDING HUNGRY OHIOANS, BUT HELPING LOCAL FARMERS, GROWERS AND COMMODITY PRODUCERS BY CLEARING THEIR UNMARKETABLE -- THOUGH INCREDIBLY WHOLESOME -- PRODUCTS AND DISTRIBUTING THEM THROUGH A NETWORK OF OVER 3,000 FOOD PANTRIES, SOUP KITCHENS AND OTHER EMERGENCY FOOD PROVIDERS.  

RECOGNIZING THAT HUNGER IS MERELY A SYMPTOM OF POVERTY, OASHF CONTINUES TO BE THE HOME OF THE OHIO BENEFIT BANK (OBB), A TECHNOLOGY-BASED MOVEMENT TO CONNECT POOR OHIOANS TO THE CRITICAL WORK SUPPORT PROGRAMS AND TAX CREDITS, INCLUDING THE EARNED INCOME TAX CREDIT.  SINCE LAUNCHING THE OHIO BENEFIT BANK IN JULY, 2006, WITH NINE AMERICORPS VISTA MEMBERS AS THE BACKBONE OF THE EFFORT, THE OBB HAS CONNECTED OVER 116,000 STRUGGLING OHIO HOUSEHOLDS -- OVER 181,000 INDIVIDUALS -- TO OVER $400 MILLION IN TAX CREDITS AND WORK SUPPORTS.

OASHF CONTINUES TO ENJOY A STRONG PARTNERSHIP WITH THE CORPORATION FOR NATIONAL AND COMMUNITY SERVICE (CNCS), FUNCTIONING AS A STATEWIDE INTERMEDIARY SPONSOR.  THIS MODEL CREATES GREAT EFFICIENCIES WITHIN CNCS BY PROVIDING A BLOCK OF SLOTS TO OASHF TO SUB-GRANT OUT TO OTHER ORGANIZATIONS WITH A MISSION TO COMBAT POVERTY.  OASHF HAS MANY YEARS OF EXPERIENCE MANAGING LARGE, STATEWIDE PROGRAMS, SO THIS MODEL HAS WORKED VERY WELL IN PREVIOUS YEARS. 

IN ORDER TO MEET THE EVER-RISING DEMAND ON THE EMERGENCY FOOD NETWORK AND THE PUBLIC BENEFITS SYSTEMS, AND TO CONTINUE TO FUNCTION AS AN INTERMEDIARY SPONSOR, OASHF RESPECTFULLY REQUESTS A SECOND YEAR OF OPERATIONAL GRANT FUNDING FOR SHARECORPS (SECOND HARVEST AMERICORPS VISTA RESOURCE AND ENGAGEMENT CORPS), TO BEGIN ON APRIL, 24, 2011.  OASHF REQUESTS A CONTINUATION GRANT TO SUPPORT A TOTAL OF 72 VISTA MEMBER SLOTS AND 3 VISTA LEADER SLOTS, WITH OASHF COST-SHARING 20 MEMBER SLOTS.  AS IN THE CURRENT PROGRAM YEAR, OASHF WILL ALLOCATE ROUGHLY HALF OF THE NON-LEADER SLOTS TO BE RELEASED TO ORGANIZATIONS OUTSIDE OF OASHF'S NETWORK THROUGH AN RFP PROCESS.  CURRENTLY, OASHF HAS PLACED MEMBERS AT NEARLY 30 ORGANIZATIONS THROUGHOUT OHIO THROUGH THE INTERMEDIARY MODEL.  PROGRAM STAFF IS CURRENTLY EVALUATING EACH SITE AND EXPECT THAT AT LEAST NINE HOST SITES WILL NOT CONTINUE INTO THE NEXT PROGRAM YEAR.  ALL OTHER HOST SITES IN GOOD STANDING WILL REAPPLY TO RETAIN THEIR SLOT THROUGH A SHORT, ONE PAGE REQUEST.  OASHF WILL CONTINUE TO ASSIGN APPROXIMATELY 30 MEMBER SLOTS TO CONTINUE THE ANTI-HUNGER WORK AT FOOD BANKS AS WELL AS TO CONTINUE TO SUPPORT THE OHIO BENEFIT BANK IN INNOVATIVE AND NEW WAYS.  

IN JANUARY, 2011, OASHF SUBMITTED A PROPOSAL TO CNCS TO EXPAND THE PROGRAM BY AT LEAST TEN MEMBER SLOTS TO CREATE A SMALL CORPS TO WORK ON CONNECTING RETURNING VETERANS TO TRAINING AND EDUCATION OPPORTUNITIES THAT WILL HELP THEM TRANSITION TO THE CIVILIAN WORKFORCE.  THIS CORPS WOULD ALSO WORK ON CONNECTING THE FAMILIES OF ACTIVE-DUTY SERVICEMEN AND WOMEN TO CRITICAL PROGRAMS AND BENEFITS.  WHILE THE EXPANSION WAS NOT APPROVED, OASHF IS STILL COMMITTED TO THIS EFFORT AND WILL ALLOCATE UP TO TEN MEMBER SLOTS TO BE SUB-GRANTED THROUGH A LIMITED RFP TARGETED TO VETERAN'S ORGANIZATIONS SUCH AS THE FIVE REGIONAL MILITARY ONE SOURCE OFFICES WHICH OFFER A WIDE VARIETY OF PROGRAMMING AND SUPPORTIVE SERVICES. award_description:
OUR LEGAL NAME IS THE UNITED WAY OF EAST MISSISSIPPI. ESTABLISHED IN MERIDIAN, MISSISSIPPI IN 1960 BY LOCAL BUSINESS AND CHURCH LEADERS, OUR ORGANIZATION IS NOW A FUNDING SOURCE FOR 14 LOCAL NON-PROFITS AS WELL AS SEVERAL IN-HOUSE COMMUNITY IMPACT PROGRAMS.  THE MISSION OF THE UNITED WAY IS TO IMPROVE LIVES BY MOBILIZING THE CARING POWER OF THE COMMUNITY THROUGH GIVING, ADVOCATING AND VOLUNTEERING.
THE UNITED WAY OF EAST MISSISSIPPI HAS BEEN A PROUD SPONSOR OF AND HAS ENJOYED A FRUITFUL PARTNERSHIP WITH THE RETIRED & SENIOR VOLUNTEER PROGRAM FOR 40 YEARS. 
WE ARE SEEKING A FUNDING REQUEST IN THE AMOUNT OF $63,690 PER YEAR FOR THE LIFE OF THIS GRANT. THE SERVICE CATEGORIES THAT RSVP WILL ADDRESS INCLUDE: CRISIS INTERVENTION; DISASTER ASSISTANCE AND PREPAREDNESS; ASSISTING SERVICE ORGANIZATIONS SUCH AS SCOUTING; THE BOYS & GIRLS CLUB; LOCAL SHELTERS; FOOD PANTRIES/MASS FEEDING AGENCIES; HEALTH/NUTRITION; FINANCIAL EMPOWERMENT PROGRAMS; AND OTHER HUMAN NEEDS. THE NEEDS IN THIS COMMUNITY THAT OUR PROJECT WILL ADDRESS ARE DEFINED IN THESE SERVICE CATEGORIES, SPECIFICALLY IN THE FOCUS AREAS OF HEALTHY FUTURES, EDUCATION, AND ECONOMIC OPPORTUNITY. 
OUR RESEARCH METHODOLOGY WILL BE BASED ON 2010 CENSUS DATA AND THE SHARING OF INFORMATION GLEANED BY COLLABORATION WITH UNITED WAY'S 14 COMMUNITY PARTNERS.  THE ANTICIPATED MEASURABLE OUTCOME FOR THIS PROJECT IS TO PROVIDE 30,000 DOCUMENTED HOURS OF COMMUNITY SERVICE PER YEAR BY APPROXIMATELY 175 SENIOR VOLUNTEERS.

award_description:
THE VOLUNTEER CENTER OF THE EAST BAY (VCEB) HAS SERVED AS A RSVP GRANTEE IN CONTRA COSTA COUNTY IN CALIFORNIA SINCE 2004. WE HAVE CREATED A DYNAMIC 55+ VOLUNTEER PROGRAM BY LEVERAGING OUR RSVP GRANT DOLLARS WITH SIGNIFICANT VCEB RESOURCES IN ORDER TO MAXIMIZE EVERY FINANCIAL INVESTMENT. OUR PRIMARY GOAL IS TO DELIVER RESULTS-DRIVEN SERVICES FROM SENIOR VOLUNTEERS TO MEET THE MOST PRESSING NEEDS OF OUR LOCAL COMMUNITIES. THESE INCLUDE FEEDING THE HUNGRY, PROVIDING RESOURCES FOR SHELTER, AND INDIVIDUAL ASSISTANCE. THIS INVESTMENT IN PROMOTING VOLUNTEERISM AMONG OLDER ADULTS IS AN INTEGRAL PART OF RSVP'S MANDATE TO IMPROVE LOCAL RESIDENTS' QUALITY OF LIFE. 
AN ESTIMATED 250 RSVP VOLUNTEERS WILL SERVE THROUGH A NETWORK OF 30 STATIONS, WHICH INCLUDE MEALS ON WHEELS/SENIOR OUTREACH SERVICES (MOW/SOS), OPPORTUNITY JUNCTION, JUNIOR ACHIEVEMENT, AND PICES EMERGENCY FOOD PANTRY. BECAUSE THE PRIMARY FOCUS AREA OF THIS PROJECT IS HEALTHY FUTURES, AT LEAST 125 VOLUNTEERS WILL BE PLACED IN ASSIGNMENTS THAT SUPPORT AGING IN PLACE, AND OBESITY AND FOOD. WITHIN THIS PRIMARY FOCUS AREA, SERVICES WILL INCLUDE PROVIDING COMPANIONSHIP TO THE FRAIL AND HOMEBOUND, TRANSPORTATION, AND FOOD DISTRIBUTION AND COLLECTION. VOLUNTEERS WILL ALSO PARTICIPATE AT ADDITIONAL AGENCIES IN ACTIVITIES SUCH AS VETERAN AND MILITARY FAMILY ASSISTANCE, VOLUNTEER RECRUITMENT, AND SUPPORT WITH JOB-TRAINING AND OTHER SKILL-DEVELOPMENT SERVICES. 
OUR RSVP PROGRAM WILL CONTINUE TO IMPLEMENT SHORT-TERM PROJECTS TO ATTRACT SENIORS LOOKING FOR INTERMITTENT VOLUNTEERING PROJECTS UTILIZING THEIR PROFESSIONAL SKILLS. THIS ADDITIONAL AVENUE OF AGENCY SUPPORT ALLOWS RSVP VOLUNTEERS TO UTILIZE DIVERSE SKILLS. AT THE END OF THE THREE-YEAR GRANT, ADULTS AND FAMILIES THAT RECEIVED SERVICES THROUGH RSVP PROGRAMS WILL HAVE BEEN PROVIDED CRITICAL FOOD AND SERVICES, AND OLDER AND HOMEBOUND ADULTS WILL REPORT HAVING INCREASED SOCIAL TIES/SOCIAL SUPPORT AND TRANSPORTATION. THE CNCS FEDERAL INVESTMENT OF $73,118 WILL BE SUPPLEMENTED BY $39,674 IN NON-FEDERAL RESOURCES.

COAHOMA OPPORTUNITIES, INCORPORATED A COMMUNITY-ACTION AGENCY, AIMS TO ASSIST LOW-INCOME CITIZENS IN BECOMING SELF SUFFICIENT AND SUSTAINABLE.  SERVING THE RURAL MISSISSIPPI DELTA REGION FOR DECADES, OUR AGENCY IS GOVERNED BY A BOARD OF DIRECTORS WHOSE PRIMARY RESPONSIBILITY IS PLANNING THE DIRECTION AND DEFINING THE FUTURE OF THE AGENCY.  THE BOARD DELEGATES TO THE EXECUTIVE DIRECTOR THE MAJOR RESPONSIBILITY AND THE AUTHORITY (DERIVED FROM THE BOARD) OF SELECTING THE SPECIFIC MEANS TO ACHIEVE THE GOALS THAT HAVE BEEN DETERMINED. 

COAHOMA OPPORTUNITIES, INCORPORATED RETIRED SENIOR VOLUNTEER PROGRAM IS REQUESTING THE FEDERAL SHARE OF 33,713 DOLLARS TO CONTINUE TO PROVIDE SERVICES TO COAHOMA COUNTY.  RESOURCES PROVIDED THROUGH THIS COMPETITIVE PROCESS ENABLES COAHOMA OPPORTUNITIES, INCORPORATED TO FURTHER SERVE COAHOMA COUNTY, SUPPORTING RETIRED SENIORS IN THEIR EFFORTS TO AID THE COMMUNITY AND ITS CITIZENS IN MAINTAINING A MEANINGFUL QUALITY OF LIFE.   COAHOMA OPPORTUNITIES INCORPORATED RETIRED SENIOR VOLUNTEER PROGRAM HAS FIVE FOCAL POINTS.  THEY ARE SCHOOL READINESS, HEAD START EARLY CHILDHOOD EDUCATION, TUTORING AND CHILDREN ELEMENTARY LITERACY, VETERANS AND FAMILIES, HEALTH EDUCATION AND OTHER HEALTH NUTRITION.  COAHOMA OPPORTUNITIES, INCORPORATED RETIRED SENIOR VOLUNTEER PROGRAM IS CONTINUOUSLY WORKING TO FULFILL THE MISSION OF CORPORATION FOR NATIONAL AND COMMUNITY SERVICES BY PROVIDING QUALITY AND TIMELY SERVICES TO THE RESIDENTS OF COAHOMA COUNTY. SOME OF THE SERVICES INCLUDE TUTORING YOUTH AND ADULTS, PROVIDING TRANSPORTATION FOR SENIORS, WITHOUT TRANSPORTATION AND OFFERING SENIOR COMPANIONSHIP FOR SENIORS WHO ARE HOME-BOUND.  COAHOMA OPPORTUNITIES INCORPORATED RETIRED SENIOR VOLUNTEER PROGRAM, THROUGH ITS MANY PARTNERSHIPS, PROVIDES OUTREACH.   OUR LONGSTANDING RELATIONSHIPS WITH CHURCHES, AGENCIES AND COMMUNITY ORGANIZATIONS HAVE ALLOWED US TO BECOME WIDELY RECOGNIZED THROUGHOUT THE COMMUNITY FOR THE WORK WE DO WITH RETIRED SENIORS. RECRUITMENT FAIRS ARE HOSTED THROUGHOUT THE COMMUNITY TO MAKE PROSPECTIVE MEMBERS AWARE OF THE PROGRAM.  THE PROJECTS OF THE COAHOMA OPPORTUNITIES, INCORPORATED RETIRED SENIOR VOLUNTEER PROGRAM ARE LED BY OUR PARTICIPANTS, WHO FULLY ENGAGES THEIR SKILLS, KNOWLEDGE AND EXPERTISE, WHICH STRENGTHENS OUR COMMUNITY AND MAKES COAHOMA COUNTY MORE LIVABLE FOR ITS RESIDENTS, ESPECIALLY SENIORS.

award_description: ACCRETING NEUTRON STARS IN LOW-MASS X-RAY BINARY SYSTEMS NS LMXBS SHOW A WIDE RANGE OF SPECTRAL PROPERTIES AND MANY TYPES OF RAPID FLUX VARIABILITY IN THE X-RAY BAND. BASED ON HOW THESE SPECTRAL AND TIMING PROPERTIES CORRELATE  THREE MAIN SUBCLASSES OF THE PERSISTENTLY BRIGHT NS-LMXBS HAVE BEEN RECOGNIZED: THE ATOLL  SOURCES  THE SCO-LIKE Z SOURCES  AND THE CYG-LIKE Z SOURCES. WHILE IT HAD LONG BEEN CLEAR THAT THE Z SOURCES ARE CONSIDERABLY MORE LUMINOUS THAN THE ATOLL SOURCES  AND HENCE ACCRETE AT MUCH HIGHER MASS ACCRETION RATES  THE RELATIVE LUMINOSITIES OF THE TWO Z SOURCE SUBCLASSES WERE NOT KNOWN. MOREOVER  THE NATURE OF THE SPECTRAL EVOLUTION ALONG THE TRACKS TRACED OUT BY Z SOURCES REMAINS A MYSTERY. PART OF THE PROBLEM WITH PAST ATTEMPTS TO MODEL THE Z SOURCE SPECTRA IS THE FACT THAT THE BROAD ENERGY COVERAGE OF THESE MISSIONS WAS PROVIDED BY TWO OR THREE DIFFERENT INSTRUMENTS  INSTEAD OF A SINGLE ONE. AS A RESULT OF THIS  THE INTERPRETATION OF THESE SPECTRA SUFFERED FROM CALIBRATION UNCERTAINTIES BETWEEN THE VARIOUS INSTRUMENTS. IN PRACTICE THIS LED TO POOR CONSTRAINTS IN THE HIGH ENERGY COMPONENTS IN THE SPECTRA. NUSTAR FOR THE FIRST TIME PROVIDES BROAD ENERGY COVERAGE FROM SINGLE INSTRUMENT (OR  TO BE PRECISE TWO NEARLY IDENTICALDETECTORS)  THEREBY REMOVING AN IMPORTANT SOURCE OF UNCERTAINTY IN THE MODELING OF NS-LMXB SPECTRA. ADDITIONALLY  NUSTAR IS MUCH MORE SENSITIVE THAN THE AFOREMENTIONED SATELLITES AT HIGH ENERGIES. WE PROPOSE THREE SHORT (25 KS) OBSERVATIONS OF THE CYG-LIKE Z SOURCE GX 5-1 WITH THE AIM OF BETTER UNDERSTANDING THE SUPER-EDDINGTON ACCRETION FLOWS ONTO NEUTRON STARS. THE GOAL OF OUR OBSERVATIONS IS TO TEST PROPOSED MODELS FOR THE SPECTRAL EVOLUTION IN THIS TYPE OF SOURCE  BY SIMULTANEOUSLY CONSTRAINING THE CONTINUUM AND REFLECTION FEATURES (IN PARTICULAR THE FE LINE) IN THE SPECTRUM. NUSTAR IS UNIQUELY CAPABLE OF DOING SO. BY OBSERVING GX 5-1 WE COMPLETE NUSTAR'S COVERAGE OF NEUTRON-STAR LOW-MASS X-RAY BINARIES ACROSS THE ENTIRE LUMINOSITY RANGE OF THIS CLASS  ALLOWING FOR A DETAILED COMPARISON BETWEEN SUBCLASSES. DATA WILL BE ANALYZED WITH THE STANDARD NUSTAR FTOOLS. OUR ANALYSIS WILL START WITH THE CREATION OF A HARDNESS-INTENSITY DIAGRAM (IN WHICH THE BRANCHES ARE BETTER SEPARATED THAN IN A COLOR-COLOR DIAGRAM). THIS WILL SERVE AS THE FOUNDATION FOR OUR SPECTRAL EXTRACTION. SPECTRA WILL THEN BE EXTRACTED FROM DIFFERENT POSITION ALONG THE Z TRACK AND THESE SPECTRA WILL BE ANALYZED USING VARIOUS SPECTRAL MODELS. THE RESEARCH OUTLINED IN THIS PROPOSAL ADDRESSES NASA'S 2014 STRATEGIC GOALS OBJECTVIE 1.6 DISCOVER HOW THE UNIVERSE WORKS  EXPLORE HOW IT BEGAN AND EVOLVED  AND SEARCH FOR LIFE ON PLANETS AROUND OTHER STARS.

award_description: IN ORDER TO INVESTIGATE HOW PRIMITIVE MATERIALS EVOLVED UNDER REALISTIC CONDITIONS IN THE SOLAR NEBULA  WE HAVE DEVELOPED A MONTE CARLO MODEL TO TRACK THE PATHS THAT INDIVIDUAL PARTICLES TOOK THROUGH A TURBULENT VISCOUS SOLAR NEBULA. SUCH INFORMATION ALLOWS US TO DETERMINE THE PHYSICAL AND CHEMICAL ENVIRONMENTS TO WHICH THESE PARTICLES WERE EXPOSED AND HOW LONG THEY RESIDED IN EACH. THIS MONTE CARLO MODEL WILL BE MERGED WITH CHEMICAL MODELS TO UNDERSTAND HOW CONDENSATION EVAPORATION  ANNEALING AMORPHIZATION  INTERNAL DIFFUSION  AND IRRADIATION WOULD HAVE DETERMINED THE PROPERTIES OF PRIMITIVE MATERIALS OVER THEIR LIFETIMES IN THE SOLAR NEBULA. WE WILL APPLY THESE MODELS SPECIFICALLY TO PROBLEMS FOR WHICH LABORATORY STUDIES HAVE YIELDED BOTH A DETAILED UNDERSTANDING OF THE CHEMICAL PROCESSING THAT OCCURS UNDER NEBULA CONDITIONS AS WELL AS THOSE FOR WHICH WE HAVE DETAILED CONSTRAINTS FROM METEORITIC AND COMETARY STUDIES. THESE INCLUDE: 1 THE THERMAL PROCESSING OF CALCIUM-ALUMINUM RICH INCLUSIONS AND THE RESULTING ELEMENTAL AND ISOTOPIC FRACTIONATIONS AS WELL AS THE ZONING OF DIFFERENT MINERALS. 2 THE FORMATION OF ORGANIC MOLECULES THROUGH IRRADIATION AND WARMING OF ICES. AND 3 THE COMPETING EFFECTS OF ANNEALING OF SILICATE GRAINS AT HIGH TEMPERATURES AND THE AMORPHIZATION DUE TO EXPOSURE AT THE SURFACE OF THE DISK TO HIGH ENERGY IONS FROM FLARES FROM THE YOUNG SUN. BY CARRYING OUT A COMPREHENSIVE STUDY OF POSSIBLE SOLAR NEBULA STRUCTURES AND EVOLUTIONARY PARAMETERS  WE WILL INVESTIGATE WHETHER THE CHEMICAL  MINERALOGICAL  AND ISOTOPIC OF METEORITIC AND COMETARY SAMPLES ARE CONSISTENT WITH THEIR FORMATION IN A TURBULENT VISCOUS DISK. THIS WORK FOCUSES ON THE PRIMARY GOAL OF THE ORIGINS OF SOLAR SYSTEMS PROGRAM AND THE BROADER GOALS OF NASA  AS IT WILL PROVIDE NEW INSIGHTS INTO THE ORIGIN OF PLANETARY MATERIALS.

award_description: THE UNIVERSITY OF FLORIDA (UF) PROPOSES A THREE-YEAR EFFORT TO DEVELOP AND IMPLEMENT FLOW FIELD OPTICAL DIAGNOSTIC AND MICROMACHINED SENSOR-BASED TECHNIQUES FOR THE DETERMINATION OF ACOUSTIC LINER SKIN FRICTION DRAG. SPECIFICALLY  THE OBJECTIVE IS TO ENHANCE NASA'S MEASUREMENT DIAGNOSTICS INFRASTRUCTURE BY IMPROVING "THE CAPABILITY TO ASSESS AERODYNAMIC AND ACOUSTIC CHARACTERISTICS OF LINERS" AS DISCUSSED IN TOPIC A.2.8 OF NASA NRA NNH10ZEA001N. TO ACHIEVE THIS GOAL  THREE-COMPONENT LASER DOPPLER VELOCIMETRY (LDV) AND HIGH-RESOLUTION 3-D STEREOSCOPIC AND STANDARD PARTICLE IMAGE VELOCIMETRY (PIV) MEASUREMENTS WILL BE PERFORMED TO CAPTURE THE VELOCITY FIELD NEAR THE LINER SURFACE IN THE UNIVERSITY OF FLORIDA GRAZING FLOW INCIDENCE IMPEDANCE DUCT (DONATED TO UF BY NASA-LANGLEY) FOR A VARIETY OF LINER DESIGN AND FLOW CONDITIONS. THESE MEASUREMENTS WILL PROVIDE INSIGHT INTO THE GLOBAL FLOW PHYSICS OF THE LINER AS WILL BE USED WITH STATIC PRESSURE MEASUREMENTS TO ESTIMATE THE LINER SKIN FRICTION VIA CONTROL VOLUME ANALYSIS. COMPLEMENTARY TO LDV AND PIV MEASUREMENTS  WE WILL ADAPT TWO DIFFERENT MICROMACHINED TRANSDUCER TECHNOLOGIES TO MAKE SHEAR STRESS MEASUREMENTS ON THE LINER SURFACE. THE FIRST SENSOR IS A DIFFERENTIAL CAPACITIVE FLOATING ELEMENT TRANSDUCER THAT WILL PROVIDE TIME-RESOLVED SHEAR STRESS DATA AT A SINGLE POINT. THE SECOND TRANSDUCER IS A VARIATION OF THE MICROPILLAR SENSORS THAT WILL PROVIDE FULL-FIELD SHEAR STRESS MEASUREMENTS OVER A FEW LINER CELLS AT AN INSTANT IN TIME. BOTH THE FLOW FIELD AND SHEAR STRESS MEASUREMENTS WILL BE MADE SIMULTANEOUSLY WITH STANDARD ACOUSTIC IMPEDANCE EDUCTION MEASUREMENTS. THE NET RESULT WILL BE AN INTEGRATED FLOW-NOISE MEASUREMENT SUITE TO ELUCIDATE THE ACOUSTIC AND AERODYNAMIC PERFORMANCE OF ENGINE NACELLE LINERS IN REALISTIC AEROACOUSTIC ENVIRONMENTS.

award_description: A 2008 MULTI-STATE PILOT STUDY SHOWED THAT PERSONS WITH SERIOUS MENTAL ILLNESS IN ARIZONA ARE DYING AS EARLY AS 32 YEARS BEFORE THEIR MENTALLY HEALTHIER COUNTERPARTS. THEY OFTEN DIE NOT FROM ANYTHING RELATED TO THEIR BEHAVIORAL HEALTH CONDITION BUT DUE TO PHYSICAL HEALTH PROBLEMS SUCH AS DIABETES, CARDIOVASCULAR DISEASE, RESPIRATORY DISEASE AND OTHER PREVENTABLE AND/OR MANAGEABLE PHYSICAL ILLNESSES. WEST YAVAPAI GUIDANCE CLINIC (WYGC) IS A NONPROFIT PROVIDER OF MENTAL HEALTH, CRISIS AND SUBSTANCE ABUSE SERVICES, WITH TREATMENT SITES BASED IN PRESCOTT AND PRESCOTT VALLEY, ARIZONA. THE PURPOSE OF OUR INTEGRATED HEALTH CARE PROGRAM IS TO IMPROVE THE PHYSICAL HEALTH STATUS OF ADULTS WITH SERIOUS MENTAL ILLNESS WHO HAVE OR ARE AT RISK FOR CO-OCCURRING PRIMARY CARE CONDITIONS AND CHRONIC DISEASES. THE PCBHI GRANT WILL ALLOW WYGC TO PROVIDE HEALTH CARE TO OUR CLIENTS WHO HAVE SERIOUS MENTAL ILLNESS WITH SPECIFIC FOCUS ON THE SUBPOPULATION OF 300+ THAT IS NOT ON MEDICAID/AHCCCS - THE ONES WHO TRULY CAN BENEFIT FROM THIS INTEGRATED HEALTH CARE MODEL THE MOST. OUR NEWLY-LAUNCHED INTEGRATED HEALTH CARE PROGRAM IS BUILT ON THREE INTEGRAL SERVICE COMPONENTS: PRIMARY CARE; CDSMP (CHRONIC DISEASE SELF-MANAGEMENT PROGRAM); AND HEALTHY LIFESTYLES (SMOKING CESSATION AND HEALTH PROMOTION GROUPS). WHILE THE TWO PREVENTIVE AND HEALTH PROMOTION COMPONENTS ARE UNDERWAY, PRIMARY CARE SERVICES ARE SCHEDULED TO BEGIN BEFORE THE END OF JUNE 2012. OUR PBHCI GOALS ARE: DEMONSTRATE IMPROVED HEALTH FOR ADULT PERSONS WITH A SERIOUS MENTAL ILLNESS; ENHANCE THE EXPERIENCE OF RECEIVING PRIMARY CARE SERVICES FOR ADULT PERSONS WITH A SERIOUS MENTAL ILLNESS; AND REDUCE THE COST OF PRIMARY CARE PROVIDED TO ADULTS WITH SERIOUS MENTAL ILLNESS.  BY RECEIVING A PBHCI GRANT, WYGC WILL BE ABLE TO SERVE PEOPLE THAT WE OTHERWISE MAY NOT BE ABLE TO SERVE: SPECIFICALLY, 200 PEOPLE IN YEAR ONE, 375 IN YEAR TWO, 475 IN YEAR THREE AND 600 IN YEAR FOUR.

award_description: THE COSMIC REIONIZATION OF HYDROGEN REMAINS ONE OF THE POORLY UNDERSTOOD AND CONSTRAINED FRONTIERS OF MODERN COSMOLOGY. CURRENT CONSTRAINTS OF REIONIZATION FROM OBSERVATIONS OF COSMIC MICROWAVE BACKGROUND AND HIGH-REDSHIFT QUASARS POINT TO A RAPID CHANGE OF THE IONIZATION STATE OF THE UNIVERSE FROM REDSHIFT AROUND 10 TO REDSHIFT ABOUT 6. THE CRUCIAL STAGE OF REIONIZATION BETWEEN THE TWO REDSHIFTS AND THE FORMATION OF FIRST GALAXIES ARE CLOSELY LINKED TO EACH OTHER. OBSERVATIONS OF GALAXIES BEYOND REDSHIFT 6  WHICH IS ONE OF THE MAJOR EFFORTS OF THE HUBBLE SPACE TELESCOPE (HST) AND ONE OF THE MAIN SCIENCE GOALS OF THE UPCOMING JAMES WEBB SPACE TELESCOPE (JWST)  CAN PROVIDE CRITICAL DATA FOR LEARNING ABOUT COSMIC REIONIZATION. WE PROPOSE A THEORETICAL AND COMPUTATIONAL INVESTIGATION TO USE LYMAN-ALPHA EMITTING GALAXIES (LAES)  WHICH CAN BE EFFICIENTLY DETECTED BEYOND REDSHIFT 6 THROUGH NARROW-BAND IMAGING  TO CONSTRAIN THE LATE STAGE OF REIONIZATION. THE LYMAN-ALPHA PHOTONS EMITTED FROM THESE GALAXIES INTERACT WITH THE CIRCUMGALACTIC AND INTERGALACTIC MEDIA  MAKING THE LYMAN-ALPHA EMISSION A SENSITIVE PROBE OF THE REIONIZATION STATE. THE PROPOSED WORK WILL COMBINE A STATE-OF-THE-ART COSMOLOGICAL REIONIZATION SIMULATION WITH AN EFFICIENT MONTE CARLO LYMAN-ALPHA RADIATIVE TRANSFER CODE TO OBTAIN DETAILED AND REALISTIC LYMAN-ALPHA EMISSION PROPERTIES OF LAES IN A LARGE SURVEY-LIKE VOLUME. OUR PRIMARY SCIENCE GOALS INCLUDE (1) STUDYING AND DESIGNING A VARIETY OF STATISTICS OF LAES TO ADDRESS HOW TO USE DIFFERENT ASPECTS OF OBSERVED LAES TO PROBE COSMIC REIONIZATION; (2) IMPLEMENTING SEVERAL PRESCRIPTIONS OF GALACTIC WINDS AND INCORPORATING DUST EFFECT TO ADDRESS THE MAJOR UNCERTAINTIES IN THE VISIBILITY OF LAES DURING REIONIZATION; (3) MAKING SPECIFIC PREDICTIONS AND FORMING MOCK LAE OBSERVATIONS TO HELP DEVELOPING OBSERVATIONAL STRATEGIES AND GUIDING OBSERVATIONAL EFFORTS. THE PROPOSED COMPREHENSIVE LYMAN-ALPHA RADIATIVE TRANSFER MODELING OF STAR-FORMING GALAXIES IN A COSMOLOGICAL VOLUME ACROSS THE REIONIZATION EPOCH WILL PROVIDE A SOLID THEORETICAL BASIS TO INTERPRET OBSERVATIONS AND TO CONSTRAIN COSMIC REIONIZATION  ADVANCING OUR UNDERSTANDING AND MODELING OF EARLY STRUCTURE FORMATION IN THE UNIVERSE. IT WILL PROVIDE SUPPORT TO NASA'S CURRENT AND FUTURE SPACE MISSIONS (E.G.  HST AND JWST)  AS WELL AS LARGE GROUND-BASED FACILITIES AND SURVEYS. THE DATA CUBE GENERATED FROM THIS STUDY WILL BE MADE AVAILABLE TO THE SCIENTIFIC COMMUNITY FOR A VARIETY OF APPLICATIONS.

award_description: GROUND-BASED MODELS OF WEIGHTLESSNESS AND MICROGRAVITY HAVE PROVIDED VALUABLE INSIGHTS INTO HOW DYNAMIC PHYSIOLOGICAL SYSTEMS ADAPT OR REACT TO REDUCED LOADING. ALMOST ALL OF THESE MODELS HAVE USED RODENT HIND LIMB SUSPENSION AS THE MEANS TO SIMULATE MICROGRAVITY ON ISOLATED PHYSIOLOGICAL SYSTEMS. UNFORTUNATELY  RESULTS DERIVED FROM THESE STUDIES ARE SIGNIFICANTLY LIMITED WHEN ONE TRIES TO TRANSLATE THEM TO THE HUMAN CONDITION DUE TO SIGNIFICANT ANATOMICAL AND PHYSIOLOGICAL DIFFERENCES BETWEEN RODENTS AND HUMANS.THIS IS ESPECIALLY RELEVANT WITH REGARD TO STUDYING ORTHOPAEDIC ISSUES RELATED TO BONE MAINTENANCE AND FRACTURE HEALING DURING SPACEFLIGHT. THEREFORE  IT IS CLEAR THAT A NOVEL ANIMAL MODEL OF GROUND-BASED WEIGHTLESSNESS THAT IS DIRECTLY TRANSLATABLE TO THE HUMAN CONDITION NEEDS TO BE DEVELOPED IN ORDER FOR SUBSTANTIAL PROGRESS TO BE MADE IN OUR KNOWLEDGE OF HOW MICROGRAVITY AFFECTS FRACTURE HEALING. IN LIGHT OF THIS  WE PROPOSE THE FOLLOWING FOUR SPECIFIC AIMS: (1) DEVELOP A GROUND-BASED  OVINE MODEL OF BONE UNLOADING IN ORDER TO SIMULATE FULL WEIGHTLESSNESS  (2) INTERROGATE THE EFFECTS OF A SIMULATED MICROGRAVITY ENVIRONMENT ON BONE FRACTURE HEALING USING THIS LARGE ANIMAL MODEL  (3) DEVELOP A COMPUTATIONAL MODEL OF WEIGHTBEARING IN OVINE BONE UNDER DIFFERENT EXPERIMENTAL CONDITIONS IN ORDER TO CHARACTERIZE THE LOADS EXPERIENCED BY THE FRACTURE SITE  AND (4) DEVELOP TREADMILL PROTOCOLS THAT ENHANCE BONE FRACTURE HEALING IN THE PRESENCE OF SIMULATED MICROGRAVITY. SUCCESSFUL COMPLETION OF THIS PROJECT WILL SUBSTANTIALLY ELEVATE OUR UNDERSTANDING OF HOWFRACTURE SITE LOADING AFFECTS THE SUBSEQUENT HEALING CASCADE IN THE PRESENCE OF MICROGRAVITY AND WILL FORM THE FOUNDATION FOR DESIGNING FUTURE REHABILITATION PROTOCOLS TO FACILITATE BONE HEALING DURING LONG-DURATION SPACEFLIGHT.

award_description: A TEAM OF OCEANOGRAPHERS AND GLACIOLOGISTS PROPOSE TO LEVERAGE KEY NASA ASSETS TO VASTLY IMPROVE THE SCIENCE OF GREENLAND ICE SHEET (GRIS) MASS CHANGES. THE WORK CONSISTS OF CONNECTING OBSERVATIONS AND MODELING OF THE LARGE-SCALE CIRCULATION TO THE DETAILED PROCESSES AT THE ICE SHEET-OCEAN INTERFACE. AT THE HEART OF THE MODELING ARE THE MIT OCEAN GENERAL CIRCULATION MODEL (MITGCM)  JPL&UCI'S ICESHEET SYSTEM MODEL (ISSM)  AND THE STATE ESTIMATION INFRASTRUCTURE DEVELOPED BY THE NASA-FUNDED "ESTIMATING THE CIRCULATION AND CLIMATE OF THE OCEAN" (ECCO) CONSORTIUM. VARIOUS SATELLITE DATA ALREADY USED IN ECCO AND ISSM  NEW DATA BECOMING AVAILABLE THROUGH NASA'S OPERATION ICEBRIDGE  TOGETHER WITH DEDICATED IN-SITU OBSERVATIONS NEAR GREENLAND WILL BE USED FOR AN IMPROVED SYNTHESIS  AND WILL BE LINKED TO DETAILED PROCESS STUDIES. THE FOLLOWING COMPONENTS ARE BEING PROPOSED: 1. LARGE-SCALE MODEL-DATA SYNTHESES OF THE ARCTIC OCEAN AND SUBPOLAR GYRE THAT ARE BEING DEVELOPED WITHIN ECCO SERVE AS A BASELINE TO ASSESS DECADAL VARIABILITY OF GREENLAND-BOUND SOURCE WATERS; EMPHASIS WILL BE PLACED ON ASSESSING THE SKILL OF THE ESTIMATES IN TERMSOF RESIDUAL MISFITS TO SATELLITE AND IN-SITU (PRESENT AND HISTORICAL) OBSERVATIONS NEAR THE GRIS.  2. ENHANCED RESOLUTION IS REQUIRED TO RESOLVE KEY PROCESSES ON THE CONTINENTAL SHELF AND IN KEY FJORDS WHERE MAJOR GLACIERS ARE IN CONTACT WITH OCEAN WATERS; WE WILL CONDUCT AN UNPRECEDENTED 2 KM HORIZONTAL RESOLUTION CIRCUM-GREENLAND OCEAN-SEA ICE SIMULATION WHICH WILL SERVE AS BOUNDARY CONDITION FOR COUPLING THE LARGE-SCALE CIRCULATION WITH THE SHELF AND FJORD-SCALE CIRCULATION.  3. ATMOSPHERIC REANALYSIS PRODUCTS PROVIDE BEST ESTIMATES OF THE METEOROLOGY BUT LACK THE RESOLUTION AND FIDELITY THAT ARE TARGETED NEAR THE MARINE MARGIN. EXISTING PRODUCTS FROM GLOBAL AND REGIONAL PROJECTS WILL BE ANALYZED IN TERMS FIDELITY AT LOCAL SCALES. WE WILL INVESTIGATE WHETHER THE APPARENT ATMOSPHERIC VARIABILITY CAN BE RELATED TO OBSERVED FJORD-SHELF VARIABILITY  AND TO OBSERVED GLACIER FLOWSPEED AND THINNING.  4. PROCESS STUDIES ARE PROPOSED FOR TWO GLACIER/FJORD SYSTEMS IN EAST GREENLAND  79NORTH GLACIER/FJORD AND HELHEIM GLACIER/SERMILIK FJORD  WHICH COVER A VARIETY OF RELEVANT CHARACTERISTICS (LARGE DRAINAGE BASINS; VERTICAL VERSUS SLANTED OCEAN-ICE INTERFACE; LARGE VERSUS SMALL BASAL RUNOFF). THE USE OF HYDROGRAPHIC AND  WHERE POSSIBLE  REMOTE SENSING OBSERVATIONS WILL PROVIDE A QUANTITATIVE BASIS FOR LINKING LOCAL PROCESSES TO LARGE-SCALE CIRCULATION CHANGES.  5. BASED ON CIRCUM-GREENLAND-FORCED FJORD SIMULATIONS AND MELT RATE ESTIMATES  TRANSIENT ISSM SIMULATIONS WILL BE PERFORMED TO ASSESS IMPLICATIONS FOR ICE SHEET CHANGES. SEVERAL CRITICAL ISSM IMPROVEMENTS WILL IMPLEMENTED  INCLUDING CALVING FRONT DYNAMICS. SENSITIVITY CALCULATIONS WILL BE PERFORMED IN CONJUNCTION WITH DATA COLLECED AT THE TWO PROCESS REGIONS TO ASSESS DYNAMIC THINNING AND GLACIER FRONT RETREAT IN RESPONSE TO LARGE-SCALE OCEANIC AND CLIMATE VARIABILITY.  6. THE AVAILABLE DATA  IMPROVED MODEL-DATA SYNTHESIS  AND ATMOSPHERIC FIELDS WILL BE USED IN CONJUNCTION TO TEST THE DECADAL PROGRESSION OF REGIONAL WARMING  ICE-OCEAN MELTING  AND MASS LOSS. IMPROVED ICEBRIDGE FJORD BATHYMETRY  SATELLITE AND GPS MEASUREMENTS OF THE GLACIER TERMINI  TOGETHER WITH ICE-OCEAN BOUNDARY CONDITIONS SHOULD HELP TO VASTLY IMPROVE THE SIMULATED ICE FLOW CHANGES OF OUTLETGLACIERS IN RESPONSE TO PERTURBATIONS. THE IMPACT OF ABOVE OCEANIC AND ATMOSPHERIC PROCESSES ON GRIS WILL BE STUDIED USING THE ISSM.  SENSITIVITY EXPERIMENTS WILL BE CARRIED OUT IN ORDER TO STUDY LINKAGES BETWEEN OPEN-OCEAN  FJORD CIRCULATION  ATMOSPHERIC PROCESSES  AND CHANGES ON THE ICE SHEET. THESE SENSITIVITY EXPERIMENTS WILL BE USED TO QUANTIFY WHAT NEEDS TO BE MEASURED AND WITH WHAT ACCURACY INORDER TO MAKE IMPROVED STATEMENTS ABOUT ONGOING AND FUTURE ICE SHEET EVOLUTION SCENARIOS.

award_description:
EXECUTIVE SUMMARY

 CONSEJO DE SALUD DE PUERTO RICO, INC./MED CENTRO?(CSPR) IS A NON PROFIT COMMUNITY BASED CORPORATION WITH IRS 501 (C) (3) STATUS AND IS LOCATED IN PONCE, PUERTO RICO. ITS MISSION IS: CSPR IS A COMMUNITY COMPREHENSIVE PRIMARY HEALTHCARE ORGANIZATION DEDICATED TO PROVIDING QUALITY PATIENT CARE WITH UNRELENTING ATTENTION TO CLINICAL EXCELLENCE, PATIENT SAFETY AND AN UNPARALLELED PASSION AND COMMITMENT TO ASSURE THAT THE VERY BEST HEALTHCARE, ANCILLARY AND SUPPORT SERVICES ARE PROVIDED TO THOSE WE SERVE, WHICHEVER THEIR SOCIO-ECONOMIC STANDING IS. CSPR BOARD OF DIRECTORS COMPRISES 13 MEMBERS AND THE EXECUTIVE DIRECTOR.  CSPR HAS OVER 21 YEAR'S PREVIOUS EXPERIENCE IN THE PROPOSED PROGRAM AREA. IT HAS OPERATED 3 CNCS PROGRAMS SINCE 1990. CURRENTLY, CSPR HAS 38 VSYS AND FOR YEAR 2015 IS PROPOSING TO RECRUIT 38 VSYS. THE DOLLAR AMOUNT REQUESTED IS $161.164, REPRESENTING 12 MONTHS OF FUNDING. THE SERVICE CATEGORY IS INDEPENDENT LIVING AND RESPITE CARE. THE COMMUNITY NEEDS ISSUES ADDRESS THE FACT THAT OLDER ADULTS LIVING INDEPENDENTLY NEED  DAILY TASKS SERVICES AS TO BE ABLE TO REMAIN IN THEIR HOMES WHILE CAREGIVERS NEED RESPITES SERVICES TO INCREASE SOCIAL TIES. A SURVEY-BASED METHODOLOGY RESEARCH, WITH THE PURPOSE OF DEMONSTRATING COMPLIANCE, GOALS AND OBJECTIVE ACHIEVEMENTS TRENDS, WILL BE CONDUCTED AND REPORTED QUARTERLY.  DATA GATHERED DURING PROGRAM ASSESSMENT IS TO BE ANALYZED BY EACH VOLUNTEER'S SUPERVISOR AND SUBMITTED TO THE PROJECT MANAGER AS TO MEASURE OVERALL PERFORMANCE AND DEGREE OF FULFILLMENT OF STATED GOALS AND OBJECTIVES. THE PROJECT'S ANTICIPATED OUTCOMES AIM TO SUPPLY THE NEEDS OF THE NUMBER OF HOMEBOUND OLDER ADULTS AND INDIVIDUALS WITH DISABILITIES WHO REPORT HAVING INCREASED SOCIAL TIES/PERCEIVED SOCIAL SUPPORT. THE PROJECT IS ALSO AIMED TO SUPPLY THE NEEDS OF THE NUMBER OF CAREGIVERS RECEIVING RESPITE SERVICES, IN ORDER TO PROVIDE TEMPORARY RELIEF FROM THE STRESSES OF CAREGIVING.

award_description: U.S. PARTICIPATION IN THE EXTREME UNIVERSE SPACE OBSERVATORY ON THE JAPANESE EXPERIMENT MODULE. THIS IS THE LEAD INSTITUTION PROPOSAL SUBMITTED BY THE UNIVERSITY OF CHICAGO FOR THE U.S. PARTICIPATION IN THE EXTREME UNIVERSE SPACE OBSERVATORY ON THE JAPANESE EXPERIMENT MODULE. WE PROPOSE TO DISCOVER THE ORIGIN OF EXTREME ENERGY COSMIC RAYS  THOSE WITH ENERGIES IN EXCESS OF 60 EEV  PRODUCED BY THE MOST POWERFUL COSMIC ACCELERATORS IN THE UNIVERSE. WE WILL USE THE EXTREME-UNIVERSE SPACE OBSERVATORY (EUSO) INSTRUMENT  WHICH IS TO BE ATTACHED TO THE JAPANESE EXPERIMENT MODULE (JEM) ON THE INTERNATIONAL SPACE STATION (ISS). JEM-EUSO IS BEING DEVELOPED BY AN INTERNATIONAL COLLABORATION FOR LAUNCH ON THE JAPANESE H2 TRANSFER VEHICLE IN 2017. THIS PROPOSAL IS FOR THE US CONTRIBUTION TO THE MISSION WHICH CONSISTS OF MONITORING AND CALIBRATION WITH A GLOBAL LIGHT SYSTEM (GLS) OF LASERS AND XENON LIGHT SOURCES  DATA ACQUISITION AND ANALYSIS SOFTWARE  DATA ARCHIVING  AND SCIENCE RESULTS FOR THE FIRST YEAR OF THE MISSION. WE ALSO PROPOSE THAT NASA MAKE A CONTRIBUTION TO THE UPMASS NEEDED TO LAUNCH JEM-EUSO AND ATTACHMENT POINT RESOURCES. THE GLS FOR JEM-EUSO WILL BE LOCATED AT 12 SITES AROUND THE WORLD  SUPPLEMENTED WITH AN AIRCRAFT SYSTEM. THE CALIBRATED UV LASERS AND XENON FLASH LAMPS WILL GENERATE CALIBRATED OPTICAL SIGNATURES IN THE ATMOSPHERE WITHIN THE FIELD OF VIEW OF JEM-EUSO WITH SIMILAR CHARACTERISTICS TO THE OPTICAL SIGNALS OF COSMIC RAY EXTENSIVE AIR SHOWERS. THROUGHOUT ITS PIONEERING MISSION  JEM-EUSO WILL RECONSTRUCT THE POINTING DIRECTIONS OF THE LASERS AND THE ENERGY OF THE LASERS AND FLASH LAMPS TO MONITOR THEDETECTOR'S TRIGGERS  AND ACCURACY OF ENERGY AND DIRECTION RECONSTRUCTION. THESE ARE THE CRITICAL PARAMETERS FOR IDENTIFYING THE SOURCES OF THE HIGHEST ENERGY COSMIC RAYS AND FOR EVALUATING THE SCIENTIFIC PERFORMANCE OF THIS PIONEERING INSTRUMENT. STARTING IN 2014  A PROTOTYPE OF THE JEM-EUSO INSTRUMENT WILL BE FLOWN ON A BALLOON TO TEST ITS DESIGN. WE PROPOSE TO BUILD PROTOTYPES OF THE GLS ANDUSE THEM TO TEST AND CALIBRATE THE BALLOON-BORNE PROTOTYPE  NAMED EUSO-BALLOON  DURING ITS FLIGHTS.

award_description: PUERTO RICAN COMMITTEE PROPOSES THE WOMEN'S WELLNESS & RECOVERY CARE (WWRC) PROGRAM. THIS PROGRAM WILL OFFER AN INNOVATIVE  COMBINATION OF EVIDENCE-BASED PRACTICES DESIGNED TO ENGAGE MEMBERS OF THE POPULATION OF FOCUS, ENHANCE THEIR READINESS TO RECOVERY, CASE MANAGE/NAVIGATE THEM INTO SUD/COD TREATMENT  AND PRIMARY CARE/ART FOR HIV/HCV (IF INFECTED), AND PEER-BASED RECOVERY SUPPORT SERVICES. THE WWRC WILL UTILIZE THE FOLLOWING EVIDENCE-BASED PRACTICES: MI, RESPECT, SEEKING SAFETY, PSYMED, AND YALE UNIVERSITY'S PROGRAM FOR RECOVERY & COMMUNITY HEALTH RECOVERY COACHING MODEL. THE MAIN OBJECTIVE OF THIS INTEGRATED APPROACH IS TO SIGNIFICANTLY DECREASE SUBSTANCE ABUSE, HIV/HCV TRANSMISSION, SEXUAL AND DRUG RELATED HIV/HCV RISK BEHAVIORS, THEREBY IMPROVING THE HEALTH OUTCOMES AND DECREASING HEALTH DISPARITIES AMONG BLACK LATINA WOMEN IN ESSEX AND UNION COUNTIES, NJ. PROCEED WILL ENGAGE A TOTAL OF 840 POF MEMBERS IN CTR/RESPECT IN ORDER TO SERVE 280 UNIQUE INDIVIDUALS IN EXPANDED AND ENHANCED SUBSTANCE ABUSE TREATMENT OVER THE 3 YEAR PROJECT PERIOD. PROCEED WILL COLLABORATE WITH THE INFECTIOUS DISEASES PRACTICE CLINIC OF THE UNIVERSITY OF MEDICINE & DENTISTRY OF NEW JERSEY, TRINITAS REGIONAL MEDICAL CENTER, AND FAMILY & CHILDREN SERVICES, INC.

THESE REGIONS HAVE RAMIFICATIONS FOR LONGSTANDING ISSUES IN CLIMATE SCIENCETHAT AFFECT MUCH OF THE GLOBAL POPULATION  SOMETIMES IN DEVASTATING WAYS  INCLUDING DIFFICULTIESFORECASTING BEHAVIOR OF THE MONSOON  MJO  ENSO AND TROPICAL CYCLONE INTENSITY. award_description: LARGE LENGTH SCALE CAPILLARY FLOWS IN INTERIOR COMERS HAVE AN ESTABLISHED PLACE IN FLUIDSHANDLING OPERATIONS IN REDUCED GRAVITY ENVIRONMENTS. SUCH FLOWS ARE DRIVEN BY WETTING CONDITIONS AND THE OFTEN COMPLICATED GEOMETRY OF THE SYSTEM. A QUANTITATIVE AND FUNDAMENTAL UNDERSTANDING OF COMER FLOWS IS ESSENTIAL FOR THE MYRIAD FLUIDS MANAGEMENTTASKS ABOARD SPACECRAFT INCLUDING FLOWS IN LIQUID PROPELLANT AND CRYOGEN STORAGE SYSTEMS  LIFE SUPPORT SYSTEMS  PHASE-CHANGE THERMAL SYSTEMS FOR TEMPERATURE CONTROL AND POWER PRODUCTION  AND FOR MATERIALS AND BIOFLUIDS PROCESSING. RECENT ADVANCES IN THE ANALYSIS OF CAPILLARY FLOWS IN CONTAINERS WITH INTERIOR COMERS NOWPERMIT THE CLOSED FORM PREDICTION OF FLOWS IN A VARIETY OF PLANAR AND NONPLANAR COMERS  2-D COMER NETWORKS  AND WEAKLY 3-D CONTAINERS SUCH AS CYLINDERS WITH IRREGULAR POLYGONALSECTIONS AND CYLINDERS WITH COMPLEX VANED SECTIONS MODELS FOR CURRENT PROPELLANT MANAGEMENT DEVICES. THE ANALYTICAL SOLUTIONS SERVE AS DESIGN TOOLS THAT CAN SIGNIFICANTLYREDUCE THE DESIGN CYCLE TIME FOR LOW-G CAPILLARY SYSTEMS AND ALLOW NEW INSIGHTS INTO FLOW MECHANISMS LEADING TO DESIGNS WITH IMPROVED PERFORMANCE AND RELIABILITY WITHOUT A MASS PENALTY. IN THE CURRENT INVESTIGATION  THREE RESEARCH PATHS ARE PURSUED FOR THE 3 YEAR EFFORT ANTICIPATED: CAPILLARY FLOWS AND PHENOMENA  THE CAPILLARY FLOW EXPERIMENTS (CFE-1 AND CFE-2) ABOARD ISS  AND THE CAPILLARY CHANNEL FLOWS (CCF) EXPERIMENT A JOINT GERMANY-USA EXPERIMENT. THIS PROPOSAL REQUESTS SUPPORT TO CONTINUE GROUND-BASED RESEARCH IN SUPPORT OF FLIGHT EXPERIMENTS CFE-1  CFE-2  AND CCF: CFE-1 OF WHICH HAS BEEN COMPLETED ON ISS AND WITH TWO MORE PUBLICATIONS EXPECTED AND CFE-2 WHICH ISNOW IN THE FULL ISS EXPERIMENT STAGE WITH MORE EXPERIMENTS PLANNED WITH NEW TEST CELL BEING LAUNCHED TO ISS SHORTLY. CCF IS ALSO SCHEDULED FOR A THIRD AND FOURTH ROUND OFEXPERIMENTS ON ISS DURING THE 2012-2013 TIME FRAME. FOR THE CAPILLARY FLOW WORK IN GENERAL  ANALYTICAL SOLUTIONS OF LARGE LENGTH SCALE CAPILLARY DRIVEN FLOWS IN SYSTEMS OFINCREASED GEOMETRIC COMPLEXITY ARE PURSUED: THESE INCLUDE FLOWS WITHIN SYSTEMS OF NONIDEALIZED COMERS  BIFURCATING AND COALESCING FLOWS IN CORNER NETWORKS  MULTIDIMENSIONALIMBIBITION  AND PASSIVELY PHASES SEPARATING FLOWS. PARTICULARLY WHEN BUBBLES ARE PRESENT  SUCH FLOWS ARE UNIQUE TO THE LOW-G ENVIRONMENT  COMMONPLACE IN SPACECRAFT FLUID SYSTEMS  AND ADVANTAGEOUS IF EXPLOITED  YET AT TIMES OVERLOOKED DURING SYSTEM DEVELOPMENT. IN THIS WORK  USEFUL ANALYTIC EXPRESSIONS FOR KEY FLOW CHARACTERISTICS SUCH ASTRANSIENT INTERFACE SHAPE  FLOW RATE  AND STABILITY WILL BE DETERMINED. DROP TOWER EXPERIMENTS ARE PROPOSED TO SUPPORT THE THEORETICAL ANALYSES. THOUGH THE PROPOSED RESEARCH IS FUNDAMENTAL IN TERMS OF ANALYSIS AND EXPERIMENTAL VERIFICATION  EACH PROBLEM TO BE ADDRESSED HAS BROAD APPLICATION TO FLUIDS MANAGEMENT IN LOW-G AND TERRESTRIALENVIRONMENTS. FLIGHT EXPERIMENT DATA FROM CFE-2 OPERATIONS ABOARD ISS IS  HAS AND WILL CONTINUE TO BE COLLECTED AND PUBLISHED. CCF WILL ALSO BE SUPPORTED  CREW AND EXPERIMENTPROCEDURES SPECIFIED  AND ALL CRITICAL REVIEWS AND EXPERIMENT OPERATIONS SUPPORTED THROUGH COMPLETION OF THE EXPERIMENT.

award_description: THE RSVP OF DOUGLAS COUNTY IS AN INTEGRAL PART OF UNITED COMMUNITY ACTION NETWORK (UCAN), THE DESIGNATED COMMUNITY ACTION AGENCY SERVING ROSEBURG, OREGON AND POCKET COMMUNITIES WITHIN DOUGLAS COUNTY.  RSVP OF DOUGLAS COUNTY PROVIDES A SERVICE COMPONENT NECESSARY TO ADDRESS A GROWING AGING POPULATION, VETERAN HUB AND FUNDAMENTALLY INCREASING CAPACITY FOR OUR COMMUNITY PARTNERS. AN ESTIMATED VOLUNTEER CORPS OF 470 WILL PROVIDE ACTIVE SERVICES TO VETERANS, SENIORS, DISABLED, LOW INCOME FAMILIES AND INDIVIDUALS THAT INCREASE SELF-SUFFICIENCY, INCREASE COMMUNITY HEALTH AND WELLNESS, SECURE BENEFITS FOR ECONOMIC STABILIZATION, EDUCATE TO STRENGTHEN CONSUMER PROTECTION AND ADVOCATE FOR REMOVAL OF BARRIERS TO INDEPENDENT LIVING. THE CNCS FEDERAL INVESTMENT OF $53,216 WILL BE SUPPLEMENTED BY APPROXIMATELY $ 49,956, FUNDS INVESTED FROM THE LOCAL, STATE AND PRIVATE SECTOR.  SPONSOR UCAN, FOUNDED IN 1969 IN ROSEBURG, OREGON BY A GROUP OF THREE WOMEN, THEN CALLED "WELFARE MOMS", AND TWO CASEWORKERS WHO WANTED MORE FOR THEIR CHILDREN HAVE A 45 YEAR HISTORY OF SERVICES AND COMMITMENT TO THE UTILIZATION OF NATIONAL SERVICE TO BUILD CAPACITY, INCREASE CIVIC ENGAGEMENT AND MAXIMIZE THE EFFORTS OF VOLUNTEERISM IN COMMUNITY OBJECTIVES. UCAN AS AN AGENCY OPERATES THROUGHOUT DOUGLAS AND JOSEPHINE COUNTIES WITH A STAFF OF MORE THAN 190 PEOPLE COMMITTED TO PROMOTING RESOURCES AND OPPORTUNITIES THAT INCREASE THE SELF-RELIANCE OF ALL LOW INCOME FAMILIES AND INDIVIDUALS. THROUGH THE OPERATION OF RSVP AS A  UCAN SPONSORED PROGRAM, AND OUR COLLABORATION WITH COMMUNITY BASED ORGANIZATIONS AND AGENCIES, OUR GOAL IS TO ALLEVIATE POVERTY AND POSITIVELY IMPACT THE QUALITY OF LIFE FOR ELDERLY, POOR, AND DISABLED INDIVIDUALS IS ESTABLISHED AS A STRONG, SHARED MISSION ON BEHALF OF THE CITIZENS OF DOUGLAS COUNTY.

award_description: THE MASS EXTINCTION AT THE CRETACEOUS/PALEOGENE (K/PG) BOUNDARY HAD A DRASTIC IMPACT ON MARINE ECOSYSTEMS. A CONSIDERABLE BODY OF EVIDENCE SUPPORTS THE IMPACT AT CHICXULUB AS THE ULTIMATE TRIGGER OF THE MASS EXTINCTION  BUT THE DYNAMICS OF THE SUBSEQUENT RECOVERY ARE STILL NOT ENTIRELY UNDERSTOOD. THE DOMINANT SKELETONIZED PHYTOPLANKTON GROUPS AT THIS TIME INCLUDE THE CALCAREOUS NANNOPLANKTON  DINOFLAGELLATES AND DIATOMS. THE CALCAREOUS NANNOPLANKTON WERE DECIMATED WITH APPROXIMATELY 85% OF GENERA AND 93% OF SPECIES GOING EXTINCT. HOWEVER  DIATOMS HAD ~85% SURVIVAL ACROSS THE BOUNDARY AND DINOFLAGELLATES ACTUALLY INCREASED IN DIVERSITY. THESE NON-CALCAREOUS PLANKTON MOST LIKELY SURVIVED BECAUSE OF THEIR ABILITY TO FORM STRESS-RESISTANT RESTING CYSTS AND BECAUSE THEY WERE BETTER ADAPTED TO HIGH-STRESS ENVIRONMENTS. AS PART OF EXOBIOLOGY GRANT NNX07AK62 A LARGE  GLOBAL DATABASE OF NANNOPLANKTON ASSEMBLAGES ACROSS THE K/PG BOUNDARY WAS COMPILED LEADING TO THE DISCOVERY THAT THE NORTHERN HEMISPHERE OCEANS SUFFERED HIGHER NANNOPLANKTONEXTINCTION RATES THAN THE SOUTHERN HEMISPHERE WITH AN ECOLOGICAL "CRISIS" THAT LASTED FOR APPROXIMATELY 350 THOUSAND YEARS AFTER THE IMPACT. HOWEVER  NO STUDY HAS COMBINED ALL OF THE SKELETONIZED PLANKTON INTO A SINGLE INVESTIGATION TO DETERMINE HOW NON-CALCAREOUS PLANKTON INFLUENCED THE OCEANIC RECOVERY. THIS STUDY IS DESIGNED TO ASSESS HOW DIATOM  DINOFLAGELLATES AND NANNOPLANKTON ECOSYSTEMS  ESPECIALLY THOSE ON SHELVES  WERE ADAPTED TO SURVIVAL AT THE K/PG BOUNDARY. THIS INVESTIGATION WILL DETERMINE WHETHER SOUTHERN HEMISPHERE SHELF ENVIRONMENTS OFFERED REFUGES TO PHYTOPLANKTON TAXA IN THE IMMEDIATE WAKE OF THE IMPACT  WHETHER THESE ENVIRONMENTS "SEEDED" ASSEMBLAGES DURING THE RECOVERY INTERVAL  AND WHAT THE DIFFERENCE BETWEEN DIATOMS  DINOFLAGELLATES ANDNANNOPLANKTON TELLS US ABOUT KILLING MECHANISMS AS WELL AS THE DYNAMICS OF THE RECOVERY. ECOLOGICAL RECOVERY OF ALL PHYTOPLANKTON GROUPS LIKELY TOOK PLACE ONLY AFTER THE BIOLOGIC PUMP WAS RESTORED AFTER THE K/PG EXTINCTION. THE PROPOSED STUDY IS ALSO DESIGNED TO REFINE OUR UNDERSTANDING OF HOW THE RECOVERY OF THE BIOLOGICAL PUMP CONTROLLED THE RECOVERY OF PHYTOPLANKTON ECOSYSTEMS.  NANNOPLANKTON ASSEMBLAGES WILL BE STUDIED IN SELECTED NORTHERN HEMISPHERE SHELF SECTIONS AND IN MORE NUMEROUS SOUTHERN HEMISPHERE SHELF AND DEEP-SEA SECTIONS. INVESTIGATION OF NANNOPLANKTON WILL BE SUPPLEMENTED WHEREVER POSSIBLE WITH DIATOMS ANDDINOFLAGELLATES: DIATOMS IN SOUTHERN HEMISPHERE SHELF SECTIONS AND DINOFLAGELLATES IN NORTHERN AND SOUTHERN HEMISPHERE SHELVES AND SLOPE DEPOSITS. IT IS HYPOTHESIZED THAT DIATOMS AND DINOFLAGELLATES MAY HAVE HELPED (VIA REMOVAL OF EXCESS NUTRIENTS AND METALS) OR HINDERED (VIA COMPETITION) THE RECOVERY OF NANNOPLANKTON. WE HAVE THE FOLLOWING PRIMARY HYPOTHESES TO EXPLAIN THE NATURE OF THERECOVERY: 1. EARLIEST PALEOCENE NANNOPLANKTON ORIGINATED IN THE SHELF ENVIRONMENTS AND SPREAD THROUGH THE OCEAN AFTER THE K/PG EVENT; 2. THE SHELVES OFFERED A REFUGE FOR NANNOPLANKTON AT THE BOUNDARY  AND OTHER PLANKTON GROUPS (DIATOMS AND DINOFLAGELLATES) COULD HAVE EITHER HELPED OR HINDERED THE NANNOPLANKTON RECOVERY; 3. THE BIOLOGICAL PUMP PAVED THE WAY FOR SITES TO BECOME HABITABLE BY REMOVING TOXIC METALS AND EXCESS NUTRIENTS FROM THE SURFACE OCEAN; AND 4. SURFACE ACIDIFICATION WAS NOT SEVERE ENOUGH TO CAUSEEXTINCTION  BUT METAL POISONING AMPLIFIED EXTINCTION AND PROLONGED RECOVERY. DEVELOPMENT OF A HIGH-RESOLUTION STRATIGRAPHIC FRAMEWORK IN THE NORTHERN AND SOUTHERN HEMISPHERE SHELF AND SLOPE LOCATIONS AND AT SOUTHERN HEMISPHERE DEEP-SEA SITES WILL BE THE CORNERSTONE OF THE INVESTIGATION.

award_description:
NORTH CENTRAL-FLINT HILLS AREA AGENCY ON AGING (NC-FHAAA), THE SPONSORING AGENCY FOR THE FOSTER GRANDPARENT PROGRAM IS A PRIVATE NOT FOR PROFIT AGENCY SERVING AN 18 COUNTY REGION IN CENTRAL KANSAS.  THE AGENCY'S MISSION IS "TO CREATE A COMPREHENSIVE AND COORDINATED SYSTEM OF SERVICES TO ENHANCE THE DIGNITY AND INDEPENDENCE OF OLDER KANSANS".  NC-FH AAA SPONSORED SERVICES ARE AVAILABLE TO ANY KANSAN WHO MEETS THE INCOME ELIGIBILITY REQUIREMENTS AND SERVICES ARE SPECIFICALLY TARGETED TO LOW-INCOME, LOW-INCOME MINORITY, AND FRAIL/ISOLATED OLDER KANSANS.
NC-FH AAA IS REQUESTING $203,320 TO SPONSOR THE FOSTER GRANDPARENT PROGRAM.  THE CNCS FEDERAL INVESTMENT OF $203,320 WILL BE SUPPLEMENTED WITH $22,111 OF NON FEDERAL RESOURCES.  OUR PROJECT WILL FOCUS ON K-12 SUCCESS AND SCHOOL READINESS SERVING IN ELEMENTARY PUBLIC/FAITH BASED SCHOOLS AND SCHOOL READINESS PROGRAMS IN SALINE, DICKINSON, GEARY, AND RILEY COUNTIES.   AN ESTIMATED 33 UNDUPLICATED VOLUNTEERS WILL SERVE IN A NETWORK OF 14 PUBLIC AND ONE FAITH BASED VOLUNTEER STATIONS.  THE FOSTER GRANDPARENTS WILL TUTOR-MENTOR IN THE CLASSROOMS WITH THE ASSIGNED CHILDREN FOCUSING ON LITERACY.  THE 33 FOSTER GRANDPARENTS SERVING IN ED2 K-12 SUCCESS ASSIGNMENT PLANS WILL ADDRESS LITERACY WITH THE ASSIGNED CHILDREN.  THESE FOSTER GRANDPARENTS WILL TUTOR-MENTOR ASSIGNED STUDENTS ON ASSIGNMENTS PROVIDED BY THE TEACHER UTILIZING BOOKS, FLASH CARDS, WORKSHEETS, GAMES AND OTHER ACTIVITIES TO TEACH SOUND, VOCABULARY, SPELLING AND WRITING.  TWO FOSTER GRANDPARENTS WILL SERVE IN ED21 SCHOOL READINESS PROGRAMS AT ONE VOLUNTEER STATIONS.  THE FOSTER GRANDPARENTS SERVING IN SCHOOL READINESS WORK PLANS WILL PARTICIPATE IN THE DAILY CLASSROOM ACTIVITIES DESIGNED TO INCREASE COGNITIVE AND LANGUAGE SKILLS.

award_description: THE UNIVERSITY OF KENTUCKY (UK) COLLEGE OF SOCIAL WORK (UKCOSW) WILL DEVELOP, IMPLEMENT AND FURTHER DISSEMINATE THE SBIRT TRAINING MODEL TO IDENTIFY AND INTERVENE WITH SUBSTANCE USE AMONG PATIENTS IN PRIMARY CARE AND DISCIPLINE SPECIFIC SETTINGS (E.G., DENTAL OFFICES). OVER A THREE YEAR PERIOD, 254 FACULTY, HEALTH PROFESSIONAL STUDENTS, AND COMMUNITY HEALTH PROFESSIONALS WILL BE TRAINED. IN ADDITION, SBIRT WILL BE INFUSED INTO THE SECOND YEAR UKCOSW CLINICAL SOCIAL WORK CURRICULUM.  AN EVIDENCE-BASED CURRICULUM DELIVERING REQUIRED COMPONENTS OF THE SAMHSA RESIDENCY TRAINING PROJECTS WILL BE DEVELOPED INCLUDING CONTINUING EDUCATION ACTIVITIES FOR PRACTICING HEALTH PROVIDERS AND DIDACTIC AND CLINICAL EXPERIENCES FOR UK TRAINEES IN THE UNIVERSITY OF KENTUCKY DEPARTMENT OF FAMILY AND COMMUNITY MEDICINE PRIMARY CARE PRACTICE.  ONE INNOVATION WILL LINK THE CURRICULUM AND ITS IMPLEMENTATION TO ELEMENTS OF THE PATIENT CENTERED MEDICAL HOME MODEL OF PATIENT CARE. THIS MODEL IS LIKELY TO BE REQUIRED FOR MEDICAL CARE DELIVERY SYSTEMS IN THE NEAR FUTURE. FURTHERMORE, THE PROJECT WILL PROMOTE WIDER DISSEMINATION OF SBIRT PRACTICES BY DEVELOPING CULTURAL ADAPTATIONS OF THE CURRICULUM TO MEET THE UNIQUE NEEDS OF THE RURAL APPALACHIAN POPULATION. THE PROPOSED PROJECT IS DESIGNED TO INCREASE ACCESS TO SBIRT TRAINING FOR BEHAVIORAL HEALTH WORKERS ENTERING AND CONTINUING PRACTICE IN KENTUCKY. IN CONJUNCTION WITH THE UK COLLEGE OF MEDICINE, THE UKCOSW ESTABLISHED AN INFRASTRUCTURE WITHIN THE SOCIAL WORK CONCENTRATION IN THE FORM OF AN INTEGRATED BEHAVIORAL HEALTH TRACK TO PREPARE STUDENTS IN THE NEXT THREE YEARS FOR INTEGRATED BEHAVIORAL HEALTH PRACTICE. THIS INFRASTRUCTURE WILL ALLOW FOR IN-DEPTH FIELD PRACTICUM EXPERIENCES ON PRIMARY CARE UNITS FOR 25 SOCIAL WORK STUDENTS AND 6 DFCM MEDICAL RESIDENTS ANNUALLY. HOWEVER, ADDITIONAL TRAINING WILL BE OFFERED BEYOND THESE TRAINING SITES.

award_description: RENZ ADDICTION COUNSELING CENTER (RENZ) IS A COMMUNITY BASED SUBSTANCE ABUSE TREATMENT AND HIV PREVENTION ORGANIZATION SERVING COOK, DUPAGE, AND KANE COUNTIES IN ILLINOIS. RENZ'S SISTERS UNITED IN PREVENTING AND PROTECTING OURSELVES AND/BY RECOVERING TOGETHER (SUPPORT) PROJECT WILL OFFER SUBSTANCE (SA) AND HIV PREVENTION SERVICE TO MINORITY WOMEN, WITH A PRIMARY EMPHASIS ON KANE AND WESTERN COOK AND DUPAGE COUNTIES' HISPANIC AND AFRICAN AMERICAN FEMALES, TO REDUCE BEHAVIORS THAT LEAD TO SA AND HIV INFECTION. THE PROJECT EB COMPONENTS ARE FROM SAMHSA'S TREATMENT IMPROVEMENT PROTOCOL SERIES, MI, SEEKING SAFETY, AND INTENSIVE CARE MANAGEMENT. THE CDC RESPECT INTERVENTION WILL BE USED FOR RISK REDUCTION, COUNSELING AND TESTING. THE PROJECT WILL UNITE COMMUNITY BASED AGENCIES ADDRESSING SA ISSUES, HIV PREVENTION, AND TRAUMA IN AN EFFORT TO EMPOWER WOMEN TO ADOPT HEALTHY LIFE STYLES. THE GOALS OF THE PROJECT ARE TO REDUCE SA AND HIV/HEPATITIS INFECTION AND TRANSMISSION RATES IN THE SERVICED AREA; OUTREACH TO WOMEN IMPACTED BY TRAUMA AND LINK THEM TO SA/HIV/MH INTERVENTION SERVICES; INCREASE ACCESS TO CULTURALLY SENSITIVE, FAMILY CENTERED, TRAUMA-INFORMED, SA/MH/HIV/HEPATITIS PREVENTION AND TREATMENT SERVICES FOR MINORITY WOMEN; AND TO EDUCATE AND EMPOWER MINORITY WOMEN TO ADOPT SAFE SEX PRACTICES AND MAKE INFORMED BEHAVIORAL HEALTH DECISIONS. THIS PROJECT INTENDS TO PROVIDE SA TREATMENT PLAN AND CM SERVICES TO A TOTAL OF 375 CLIENTS OVER 3 YEARS.

ARCARE IS A PRIVATE NOT-FOR-PROFIT CORPORATION DEVELOPED IN 1986 TO MEET THE PRIMARY HEALTH NEEDS OF ALL RESIDENTS IN ITS SERVICE AREA AND IS THE SPONSOR ORGANIZATION OF ARCARE RSVP.  THE MISSION OF ARCARE IS HEALTH FOR ALL WITH A FOCUS ON CUSTOMER HEALTH, COMMUNITY HEALTH, EMPLOYEE HEALTH, AND ORGANIZATIONAL HEALTH.  ARCARE HAS SUCCESSFULLY MANAGED CNCS GRANTS FOR EIGHT YEARS PLACING VOLUNTEERS AGE 55+ IN IDENTIFIED STATIONS TO MEET RESIDENT NEEDS AND USE THE SKILLS OF THE VOLUNTEERS.  
AN ESTIMATED 519 RSVP VOLUNTEERS WILL SERVE CLAY, CRAIGHEAD, CRITTENDEN, CROSS, GREENE, LAWRENCE, MISSISSIPPI, POINSETT, RANDOLPH, AND ST. FRANCIS COUNTIES IN ARKANSAS.  THIS RSVP PROPOSED SERVICE AREA IS A NEW AREA FOR ARCARE RSVP.  ACCORDING TO THE USDA, ARKANSAS SENIORS RANK 1ST, ARKANSAS CHILDREN RANK 7TH, AND ARKANSAS AS A WHOLE RANKS 2ND IN THE NATION FOR FOOD INSECURITY.  THE PRIMARY FOCUS AREA OF THIS PROJECT IS HEALTHY FUTURES AND OTHER AREAS OF DISASTER AND OTHER COMMUNITY NEEDS.  VOLUNTEER ACTIVITIES FOR THIS PROJECT WILL INCLUDE PARTNERING WITH STATE AND LOCAL PROGRAMS TO: 1) PROVIDE HOME-DELIVERED MEALS TO HOMEBOUND/ OLDER ADULTS OR DISABLED INDIVIDUALS, 2) PROVIDE SUPPORT, SERVICES, EDUCATION, AND/OR REFERRALS TO LOW-INCOME, UNEMPLOYED OR UNDEREMPLOYED INDIVIDUALS AND FAMILIES TO ALLEVIATE LONG-TERM HUNGER, 3) RECEIVE DISASTER ASSISTANCE TRAINING, AND 4) WORK IN SHORT-TERM OR SPECIFIC PROJECTS TO MEET OTHER COMMUNITY NEEDS.  ANTICIPATED OUTCOMES TO BE ACHIEVED BY THE END OF THE THREE-YEAR GRANT PERIOD ARE AS FOLLOWS:  1) NUMBER OF INDIVIDUALS RECEIVING HOME-DELIVERED MEALS REPORTING INCREASED SOCIAL TIES/PERCEIVED SOCIAL SUPPORT ALLOWING THEM TO REMAIN LIVING INDEPENDENTLY, 2) INCREASED NUMBER OF INDIVIDUALS REPORTING FOOD SECURITY OF THEMSELVES AND HOUSEHOLD MEMBERS DUE TO PROVIDED SUPPORT, SERVICES, EDUCATION, AND/OR REFERRALS TO ALLEVIATE LONG-TERM HUNGER, 3) THE NUMBER OF PERSONS PARTICIPATING IN DISASTER PREPAREDNESS TRAINING, AND 4) THE VOLUNTEERS ME THE NEED OF THE COMMUNITY ACTIVITY OR PROJECT.  THE CORPORATION FOR NATIONAL AND COMMUNITY SERVICE FEDERAL INVESTMENT OF $62,683 WILL BE SUPPLEMENTED BY $6,269 GRANTEE IN-KIND.

award_description:
COUNCIL OF CHURCHES OF THE OZARKS (CCO), SPONSOR OF THE RETIRED AND SENIOR VOLUNTEER PROGRAM (RSVP) OF SPRINGFIELD MISSOURI, IS A NON-PROFIT ORGANIZATION, SERVING THE MOST VULNERABLE PEOPLE IN OUR COMMUNITY (CHILDREN, SENIORS, THE DISABLED, AND VETERANS) BY PROVIDING A VARIETY OF SERVICES THAT MAKE A DIFFERENCE. THE MISSION IS TO CHANGE QUALITY OF LIVES "BY DOING TOGETHER WHAT CAN BEST BE DONE TOGETHER."
CCO, RSVP, IS REQUESTING $66,917 TO SUPPORT 175 UNDUPLICATED VOLUNTEERS IN THE PRIMARY FOCUS AREA (EDUCATION) AT 57 WORK STATIONS IN GREENE, CHRISTIAN, WEBSTER, AND PULASKI COUNTIES IN MISSOURI: EDUCATION DEVELOPING ACADEMIC LITERACY WITH ONE-ON-ONE TUTORING FOR 30 MINUTES A WEEK IN THE SCHOOL LIBRARIES.  COMMUNITY PRIORITIES PROVIDING CONGREGATE MEALS TO SENIORS/DISABLED.  HEALTHY FUTURES-HOME BOUND SHOPPERS DELIVERING GROCERIES TO HOMEBOUND SENIORS/DISABLED AND DAILY BREAD-DELIVERING MEALS TO SENIORS/DISABLED. VETERANS AND MILITARY FAMILIES TRANSPORTING VETERANS TO FACILITIES TO GET MEDICAL HELP. DISASTER SERVICES PROVIDING SUPPORT TO FLOOD DAMAGED HOMES AND RESIDENTS. ACCORDING TO THE ANNIE CASEY FOUNDATION'S LATEST KIDS COUNT? DATA BOOK, 1 IN 6 CHILDREN NOT READING PROFICIENTLY IN 3RD GRADE, FAIL TO GRADUATE ON TIME AND 88% OF STUDENTS WHO FAILED TO EARN A HIGH SCHOOL DIPLOMA WERE STRUGGLING READERS IN 3RD GRADE. ACCORDING TO READING RESEARCH QUARTERLY, LOW LITERACY LEVELS HAVE A STRONG CORRELATION WITH POVERTY, CRIME, AND UNEMPLOYMENT. THERE ARE APPROXIMATELY 8.3 MILLION SENIORS WHO ARE HUNGRY ON ANY GIVEN DAY IN THE UNITED STATES. ACCORDING TO AMERICAN COMMUNITY SURVEY 2010 REPORT, 8.3 % OF GREENE COUNTY RESIDENTS 65 AND OVER LIVE BELOW POVERTY. A RECENT SURVEY BY AARP, FOUND THAT 89% OF ADULTS 50 AND OVER HOPED TO REMAIN IN THEIR HOMES AS THEY AGE. APPROXIMATELY 800,000 VETERANS ARE JOBLESS, 1.4 MILLION LIVE BELOW THE POVERTY LINE, AND 1 IN EVERY 3 HOMELESS ADULT MEN IN AMERICA IS A VETERAN. LAST YEAR THERE WERE 36 CONFIRMED HOMELESS VETERANS IN GREENE COUNTY. OUR NON-FEDERAL FUNDING WILL BE AT LEAST 30% OR $28,679 FOR ORIGINAL GRANT FUNDING EXCLUDING DISASTER RELIEF FUNDING. SURVEYS WILL BE USED TO MEASURE THE OUTCOME OF THE SERVICE ACTIVITIES AND CONCLUDE A 75% INCREASE IN ACADEMIC LITERACY BY CHANGING THE LIVES OF 250 STUDENTS AT THE END OF THE 3 YEAR GRANT.
